195 /*
196  * btree_get_node_header () -
197  *
198  * return:
199  * page_ptr(in):
200  *
201  */
202 BTREE_NODE_HEADER *
203 btree_get_node_header (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_ptr)
204 {
205  RECDES header_record;
206  BTREE_NODE_HEADER *header = NULL;
207 
208  assert (page_ptr != NULL);
209 
210 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
211  (void) pgbuf_check_page_ptype (thread_p, page_ptr, PAGE_BTREE);
212 #endif
213 
214  if (spage_get_record (thread_p, page_ptr, HEADER, &header_record, PEEK) != S_SUCCESS)
215  {
216  assert_release (false);
217  return NULL;
218  }
219 
220  header = (BTREE_NODE_HEADER *) header_record.data;
221  if (header != NULL)
222  {
223  assert (header->max_key_len >= 0);
224  }
225 
226  return header;
227 }

248  if (spage_get_record (thread_p, page_ptr, HEADER, &header_record, PEEK) != S_SUCCESS)

250  assert_release (false);
251  return NULL;

254  root_header = (BTREE_ROOT_HEADER *) header_record.data;

291 /*
292  * btree_init_node_header () - insert btree node header
293  *
294  * return:
295  * vfid(in):
296  * page_ptr(in):
297  * header(in):
298  *
299  */
300 int
301 btree_init_node_header (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, PAGE_PTR page_ptr, BTREE_NODE_HEADER * header,
302  bool redo)
303 {
304  RECDES rec;
305  char rec_buf[IO_MAX_PAGE_SIZE + BTREE_MAX_ALIGN];
306 
307  assert (header != NULL);
308  assert (header->node_level > 0);
309  assert (header->max_key_len >= 0);
310 
311  /* create header record */
312  rec.area_size = DB_PAGESIZE;
313  rec.data = PTR_ALIGN (rec_buf, BTREE_MAX_ALIGN);
314  rec.type = REC_HOME;
315  rec.length = sizeof (BTREE_NODE_HEADER);
316  memcpy (rec.data, header, sizeof (BTREE_NODE_HEADER));
317 
318  if (redo == true)
319  {
320  /* log the new header record for redo purposes */
321  log_append_redo_data2 (thread_p, RVBT_NDHEADER_INS, vfid, page_ptr, HEADER, rec.length, rec.data);
322  }
323 
324  if (spage_insert_at (thread_p, page_ptr, HEADER, &rec) != SP_SUCCESS)
325  {
326  return ER_FAILED;
327  }
328 
329  return NO_ERROR;
330 }

333 /*
334  * btree_node_header_undo_log () -
335  *
336  * return:
337  * vfid(in):
338  * page_ptr(in):
339  *
340  */
341 int
342 btree_node_header_undo_log (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, VFID * vfid, PAGE_PTR page_ptr)
343 {
344  RECDES rec;
345  if (spage_get_record (thread_p, page_ptr, HEADER, &rec, PEEK) != S_SUCCESS)

347  return ER_FAILED;
348  }
349 
350  log_append_undo_data2 (thread_p, RVBT_NDHEADER_UPD, vfid, page_ptr, HEADER, rec.length, rec.data);
351 
352  return NO_ERROR;
353 }

377 /*
378  * btree_change_root_header_delta () -
379  *
380  * return:
381  * vfid(in):
382  * page_ptr(in):
383  * null_delta(in):
384  * oid_delta(in):
385  * key_delta(in):
386  *
387  */
388 int
389 btree_change_root_header_delta (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, VFID * vfid, PAGE_PTR page_ptr, int null_delta, int oid_delta,
390  int key_delta)
391 {
392  RECDES rec, delta_rec;
393  char delta_rec_buf[(3 * OR_INT_SIZE) + BTREE_MAX_ALIGN];
394  BTREE_ROOT_HEADER *root_header = NULL;
395 
396  delta_rec.data = NULL;
397  delta_rec.area_size = 3 * OR_INT_SIZE;
398  delta_rec.data = PTR_ALIGN (delta_rec_buf, BTREE_MAX_ALIGN);
399 
400  if (spage_get_record (thread_p, page_ptr, HEADER, &rec, PEEK) != S_SUCCESS)
401  {
402  return ER_FAILED;
403  }
404 
405  root_header = (BTREE_ROOT_HEADER *) rec.data;
406  root_header->num_nulls += null_delta;
407  root_header->num_oids += oid_delta;
408  root_header->num_keys += key_delta;
409 
410  /* save root head for undo purposes */
411  btree_rv_save_root_head (-null_delta, -oid_delta, -key_delta, &delta_rec);
412 
413  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVBT_ROOTHEADER_UPD, vfid, page_ptr, HEADER, delta_rec.length, rec.length,
414  delta_rec.data, rec.data);
415 
416  return NO_ERROR;
417 }

420 /*
421  * btree_pack_root_header () -
422  * return:
423  * rec(out):
424  * root_header(in):
425  *
426  * Note: Writes the first record (header record) for a root page.
427  * rec must be long enough to hold the header record.
428  */
429 static int
430 btree_pack_root_header (RECDES * rec, BTREE_ROOT_HEADER * root_header, TP_DOMAIN * key_type)
431 {
432  OR_BUF buf;
433  int rc = NO_ERROR;
434  int fixed_size = (int) offsetof (BTREE_ROOT_HEADER, packed_key_domain);
435 
436  memcpy (rec->data, root_header, fixed_size);
437 
438  or_init (&buf, rec->data + fixed_size, (rec->area_size == -1) ? -1 : (rec->area_size - fixed_size));
439 
440  rc = or_put_domain (&buf, key_type, 0, 0);
441 
442  rec->length = fixed_size + CAST_BUFLEN (buf.ptr - buf.buffer);
443  rec->type = REC_HOME;
444 
445  if (rc != NO_ERROR && er_errid () == NO_ERROR)
446  {
447  /* if an error occurs then set a generic error so that at least an error to be send to client. */
448  if (er_errid () == NO_ERROR)
449  {
450  assert (false);
451  er_set (ER_WARNING_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_GENERIC_ERROR, 0);
452  }
453  }
454 
455  return rc;
456 }

458 /*
459  * btree_init_root_header () - insert btree node header
460  *
461  * return:
462  * vfid(in):
463  * page_ptr(in):
464  * root_header(in):
465  *
466  */
467 int
468 btree_init_root_header (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, VFID * vfid, PAGE_PTR page_ptr, BTREE_ROOT_HEADER * root_header,
469  TP_DOMAIN * key_type)
470 {
471  RECDES rec;
472  char copy_rec_buf[IO_MAX_PAGE_SIZE + BTREE_MAX_ALIGN];
473 
474  assert (root_header != NULL);
475  assert (root_header->node.node_level > 0);
476  assert (root_header->node.max_key_len >= 0);
477 
478  rec.area_size = DB_PAGESIZE;
479  rec.data = PTR_ALIGN (copy_rec_buf, BTREE_MAX_ALIGN);
480 
481  if (btree_pack_root_header (&rec, root_header, key_type) != NO_ERROR)
482  {
483  return ER_FAILED;
484  }
485 
486  /* insert the root header information into the root page */
487  if (spage_insert_at (thread_p, page_ptr, HEADER, &rec) != SP_SUCCESS)
488  {
489  return ER_FAILED;
490  }
491 
492  /* log the new header record for redo purposes */
493  log_append_redo_data2 (thread_p, RVBT_NDHEADER_INS, vfid, page_ptr, HEADER, rec.length, rec.data);
494 
495  return NO_ERROR;
496 }

527 /*
528  * btree_rv_save_root_head () - Save root head stats FOR LOGICAL LOG PURPOSES
529  * return:
530  * null_delta(in):
531  * oid_delta(in):
532  * key_delta(in):
533  * recdes(out):
534  *
535  * Note: Copy the root header statistics to the data area provided.
536  *
537  * Note: This is a UTILITY routine, but not an actual recovery routine.
538  */
539 static void
540 btree_rv_save_root_head (int null_delta, int oid_delta, int key_delta, RECDES * recdes)
541 {
542  char *datap;
543 
544  assert (recdes->area_size >= 3 * OR_INT_SIZE);
545 
546  recdes->length = 0;
547  datap = (char *) recdes->data;
548  OR_PUT_INT (datap, null_delta);
549  datap += OR_INT_SIZE;
550  OR_PUT_INT (datap, oid_delta);
551  datap += OR_INT_SIZE;
552  OR_PUT_INT (datap, key_delta);
553  datap += OR_INT_SIZE;
554 
555  recdes->length = CAST_STRLEN (datap - recdes->data);
556 }
557 
558 /*
559  * btree_rv_mvcc_save_increments () - Save unique_stats
560  * return:
561  * btid(in):
562  * max_key_len(in):
563  * null_delta(in):
564  * oid_delta(in):
565  * key_delta(in):
566  * recdes(in):
567  *
568  * Note: Copy the unique statistics to the data area provided.
569  *
570  * Note: This is a UTILITY routine, but not an actual recovery routine.
571  */
572 void
573 btree_rv_mvcc_save_increments (BTID * btid, int key_delta, int oid_delta, int null_delta, RECDES * recdes)
574 {
575  char *datap;
576 
577  assert (recdes != NULL && (recdes->area_size >= ((3 * OR_INT_SIZE) + OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE)));
578 
579  recdes->length = (3 * OR_INT_SIZE) + OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE;
580  datap = (char *) recdes->data;
581 
582  OR_PUT_BTID (datap, btid);
583  datap += OR_BTID_ALIGNED_SIZE;
584 
585  OR_PUT_INT (datap, key_delta);
586  datap += OR_INT_SIZE;
587 
588  OR_PUT_INT (datap, oid_delta);
589  datap += OR_INT_SIZE;
590 
591  OR_PUT_INT (datap, null_delta);
592  datap += OR_INT_SIZE;
593 
594  recdes->length = CAST_STRLEN (datap - recdes->data);
595 }

597 /*
598  * btree_get_next_overflow_vpid () -
599  *
600  * return:
601  * page_ptr(in):
602  *
603  */
604 int
605 btree_get_next_overflow_vpid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_ptr, VPID * vpid)
606 {
607  BTREE_OVERFLOW_HEADER *ovf_header = NULL;
608 
609  ovf_header = btree_get_overflow_header (thread_p, page_ptr);
610  if (ovf_header == NULL)
611  {
612  return ER_FAILED;
613  }
614 
615  *vpid = ovf_header->next_vpid;
616 
617  return NO_ERROR;
618 }

620 /*
621  * xbtree_load_index () - create & load b+tree index
622  * return: BTID * (btid on success and NULL on failure)
623  * btid is set as a side effect.
624  * btid(out):
625  * btid: Set to the created B+tree index identifier
626  * (Note: btid->vfid.volid should be set by the caller)
627  * bt_name(in): index name
628  * key_type(in): Key type corresponding to the attribute.
629  * class_oids(in): OID of the class for which the index will be created
630  * n_classes(in):
631  * n_attrs(in):
632  * attr_ids(in): Identifier of the attribute of the class for which the index
633  * will be created.
634  * hfids(in): Identifier of the heap file containing the instances of the
635  * class
636  * unique_pk(in):
637  * not_null_flag(in):
638  * fk_refcls_oid(in):
639  * fk_refcls_pk_btid(in):
640  * fk_name(in):
641  *
642  */
643 BTID *
644 xbtree_load_index (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, BTID * btid, const char *bt_name, TP_DOMAIN * key_type, OID * class_oids,
645  int n_classes, int n_attrs, int *attr_ids, int *attrs_prefix_length, HFID * hfids, int unique_pk,
646  int not_null_flag, OID * fk_refcls_oid, BTID * fk_refcls_pk_btid, const char *fk_name,
647  char *pred_stream, int pred_stream_size, char *func_pred_stream, int func_pred_stream_size,
648  int func_col_id, int func_attr_index_start)
649 {
650  LOG_TDES *tdes = NULL;
651  SORT_ARGS sort_args_info, *sort_args;
652  LOAD_ARGS load_args_info, *load_args;
653  int cur_class, attr_offset;
654  VPID root_vpid;
655  BTID_INT btid_int;
656  PRED_EXPR_WITH_CONTEXT *filter_pred = NULL;
657  FUNCTION_INDEX_INFO func_index_info;
658  DB_TYPE single_node_type = DB_TYPE_NULL;
659  void *func_unpack_info = NULL;
660  bool has_fk;
661  BTID btid_global_stats = BTID_INITIALIZER;
662  OID *notification_class_oid;
663  bool is_sysop_started = false;
664 
665  /* Check for robustness */
666  if (!btid || !hfids || !class_oids || !attr_ids || !key_type)
667  {
668  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_BTREE_LOAD_FAILED, 0);
669  return NULL;
670  }
671 
672  sort_args = &sort_args_info;
673  load_args = &load_args_info;
674 
675  /* Initialize pointers which might be used in case of error */
676  load_args->nleaf.pgptr = NULL;
677  load_args->leaf.pgptr = NULL;
678  load_args->ovf.pgptr = NULL;
679  load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.data = NULL;
680  load_args->ovf_recdes.data = NULL;
681  load_args->out_recdes = NULL;
682  load_args->push_list = NULL;
683  load_args->pop_list = NULL;
684 
685  /*
686  * Start a TOP SYSTEM OPERATION.
687  * This top system operation will be either ABORTED (case of failure) or
688  * COMMITTED, so that the new file becomes kind of permanent. This allows
689  * us to make use of un-used pages in the case of a bad init_pgcnt guess.
690  */
691 
692  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
693  is_sysop_started = true;
694 
695  thread_p->push_resource_tracks ();
696 
697  btid_int.sys_btid = btid;
698  btid_int.unique_pk = unique_pk;
699 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
700  if (unique_pk)
701  {
702  assert (BTREE_IS_UNIQUE (btid_int.unique_pk));
703  assert (BTREE_IS_PRIMARY_KEY (btid_int.unique_pk) || !BTREE_IS_PRIMARY_KEY (btid_int.unique_pk));
704  }
705 #endif
706  btid_int.key_type = key_type;
707  VFID_SET_NULL (&btid_int.ovfid);
708  btid_int.rev_level = BTREE_CURRENT_REV_LEVEL;
709  COPY_OID (&btid_int.topclass_oid, &class_oids[0]);
710 
711  /*
712  * for btree_range_search, part_key_desc is re-set at btree_initialize_bts
713  */
714  btid_int.part_key_desc = 0;
715 
716  /* init index key copy_buf info */
717  btid_int.copy_buf = NULL;
718  btid_int.copy_buf_len = 0;
719 
720  btid_int.nonleaf_key_type = btree_generate_prefix_domain (&btid_int);
721 
722  /* Initialize the fields of sorting argument structures */
723  sort_args->lowest_active_mvccid = logtb_get_oldest_active_mvccid (thread_p);
724  sort_args->unique_pk = unique_pk;
725  sort_args->not_null_flag = not_null_flag;
726  sort_args->hfids = hfids;
727  sort_args->class_ids = class_oids;
728  sort_args->attr_ids = attr_ids;
729  sort_args->n_attrs = n_attrs;
730  sort_args->attrs_prefix_length = attrs_prefix_length;
731  sort_args->n_classes = n_classes;
732  sort_args->key_type = key_type;
733  OID_SET_NULL (&sort_args->cur_oid);
734  sort_args->n_nulls = 0;
735  sort_args->n_oids = 0;
736  sort_args->cur_class = 0;
737  sort_args->scancache_inited = 0;
738  sort_args->attrinfo_inited = 0;
739  sort_args->btid = &btid_int;
740  sort_args->fk_refcls_oid = fk_refcls_oid;
741  sort_args->fk_refcls_pk_btid = fk_refcls_pk_btid;
742  sort_args->fk_name = fk_name;
743  if (pred_stream && pred_stream_size > 0)
744  {
745  if (stx_map_stream_to_filter_pred (thread_p, &filter_pred, pred_stream, pred_stream_size) != NO_ERROR)
746  {
747  goto error;
748  }
749  }
750  sort_args->filter = filter_pred;
751  sort_args->filter_eval_func = (filter_pred) ? eval_fnc (thread_p, filter_pred->pred, &single_node_type) : NULL;
752  sort_args->func_index_info = NULL;
753  if (func_pred_stream && func_pred_stream_size > 0)
754  {
755  func_index_info.expr_stream = func_pred_stream;
756  func_index_info.expr_stream_size = func_pred_stream_size;
757  func_index_info.col_id = func_col_id;
758  func_index_info.attr_index_start = func_attr_index_start;
759  func_index_info.expr = NULL;
760  if (stx_map_stream_to_func_pred (thread_p, (FUNC_PRED **) (&func_index_info.expr), func_pred_stream,
761  func_pred_stream_size, &func_unpack_info))
762  {
763  goto error;
764  }
765  sort_args->func_index_info = &func_index_info;
766  }
767 
768  /*
769  * Start a heap scan cache for reading objects using the first nun-null heap
770  * We are guaranteed that such a heap exists, otherwise btree_load_index
771  * would not have been called.
772  */
773  while (sort_args->cur_class < sort_args->n_classes && HFID_IS_NULL (&sort_args->hfids[sort_args->cur_class]))
774  {
775  sort_args->cur_class++;
776  }
777 
778  cur_class = sort_args->cur_class;
779  attr_offset = cur_class * sort_args->n_attrs;
780 
781  /* Start scancache */
782  has_fk = (fk_refcls_oid != NULL && !OID_ISNULL (fk_refcls_oid));
783  if (heap_scancache_start (thread_p, &sort_args->hfscan_cache, &sort_args->hfids[cur_class],
784  &sort_args->class_ids[cur_class], !has_fk, false, NULL) != NO_ERROR)
785  {
786  goto error;
787  }
788  sort_args->scancache_inited = 1;
789 
790  /* After building index acquire lock on table, the transaction has deadlock priority */
791  tdes = LOG_FIND_CURRENT_TDES (thread_p);
792  if (tdes)
793  {
794  tdes->has_deadlock_priority = true;
795  }
796 
797  if (heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &sort_args->class_ids[cur_class], sort_args->n_attrs,
798  &sort_args->attr_ids[attr_offset], &sort_args->attr_info) != NO_ERROR)
799  {
800  goto error;
801  }
802  if (sort_args->filter)
803  {
804  if (heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &sort_args->class_ids[cur_class], sort_args->filter->num_attrs_pred,
805  sort_args->filter->attrids_pred, sort_args->filter->cache_pred) != NO_ERROR)
806  {
807  goto error;
808  }
809  }
810  if (sort_args->func_index_info)
811  {
812  if (heap_attrinfo_start (thread_p, &sort_args->class_ids[cur_class], sort_args->n_attrs,
813  &sort_args->attr_ids[attr_offset],
814  ((FUNC_PRED *) sort_args->func_index_info->expr)->cache_attrinfo) != NO_ERROR)
815  {
816  goto error;
817  }
818  }
819  sort_args->attrinfo_inited = 1;
820 
821  if (btree_create_file (thread_p, &class_oids[0], attr_ids[0], btid) != NO_ERROR)
822  {
823  ASSERT_ERROR ();
824  goto error;
825  }
826  btree_get_root_vpid_from_btid (thread_p, btid, &root_vpid);
827 
828  /* if loading is aborted or if transaction is aborted, vacuum must be notified before file is destoyed. */
829  vacuum_log_add_dropped_file (thread_p, &btid->vfid, NULL, VACUUM_LOG_ADD_DROPPED_FILE_UNDO);
830 
832  load_args->btid = &btid_int;
833  load_args->bt_name = bt_name;
834  db_make_null (&load_args->current_key);
835  VPID_SET_NULL (&load_args->nleaf.vpid);
836  load_args->nleaf.pgptr = NULL;
837  VPID_SET_NULL (&load_args->leaf.vpid);
838  load_args->leaf.pgptr = NULL;
839  VPID_SET_NULL (&load_args->ovf.vpid);
840  load_args->ovf.pgptr = NULL;
841  load_args->n_keys = 0;
842  load_args->curr_non_del_obj_count = 0;
843 
844  load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.area_size = BTREE_MAX_KEYLEN_INPAGE + BTREE_MAX_OIDLEN_INPAGE;
845  load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.length = 0;
846  load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.type = REC_HOME;
847  load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.data = (char *) os_malloc (load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.area_size);
848  if (load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.data == NULL)
849  {
850  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.area_size);
851  goto error;
852  }
853  load_args->ovf_recdes.area_size = DB_PAGESIZE;
854  load_args->ovf_recdes.length = 0;
855  load_args->ovf_recdes.type = REC_HOME;
856  load_args->ovf_recdes.data = (char *) os_malloc (load_args->ovf_recdes.area_size);
857  if (load_args->ovf_recdes.data == NULL)
858  {
859  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, load_args->ovf_recdes.area_size);
860  goto error;
861  }
862  load_args->out_recdes = NULL;
863 
864  /* Allocate a root page and save the page_id */
865  *load_args->btid->sys_btid = *btid;
866  btid_global_stats = *btid;
867 
868  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_LOG_BTREE_OPS))
869  {
870  _er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "DEBUG_BTREE: load start on class(%d, %d, %d), btid(%d, (%d, %d)).",
871  sort_args->class_ids[sort_args->cur_class].volid,
872  sort_args->class_ids[sort_args->cur_class].pageid,
873  sort_args->class_ids[sort_args->cur_class].slotid, sort_args->btid->sys_btid->root_pageid,
874  sort_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.volid, sort_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.fileid);
875  }
876 
877  /* Build the leaf pages of the btree as the output of the sort. We do not estimate the number of pages required. */
878  if (btree_index_sort (thread_p, sort_args, btree_construct_leafs, load_args) != NO_ERROR)
879  {
880  goto error;
881  }
882 
883  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_LOG_BTREE_OPS))
884  {
885  _er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE,
886  "DEBUG_BTREE: load finished all. %d classes loaded, found %d nulls and %d oids, "
887  "load %d keys.", sort_args->n_classes, sort_args->n_nulls, sort_args->n_oids, load_args->n_keys);
888  }
889 
890  if (sort_args->attrinfo_inited)
891  {
892  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &sort_args->attr_info);
893  if (sort_args->filter)
894  {
895  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, sort_args->filter->cache_pred);
896  }
897  if (sort_args->func_index_info)
898  {
899  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, ((FUNC_PRED *) sort_args->func_index_info->expr)->cache_attrinfo);
900  }
901  }
902  sort_args->attrinfo_inited = 0;
903  if (sort_args->scancache_inited)
904  {
905  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &sort_args->hfscan_cache);
906  }
907  sort_args->scancache_inited = 0;
908 
909  /* Just to make sure that there were entries to put into the tree */
910  if (load_args->leaf.pgptr != NULL)
911  {
912  /* Save the last leaf record */
913 
914  if (btree_save_last_leafrec (thread_p, load_args) != NO_ERROR)
915  {
916  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_BTREE_LOAD_FAILED, 0);
917  goto error;
918  }
919 
920  /* No need to deal with overflow pages anymore */
921  load_args->ovf.pgptr = NULL;
922 
923  /* Check the correctness of the foreign key, if any. */
924  if (has_fk)
925  {
926  if (btree_load_check_fk (thread_p, load_args, sort_args) != NO_ERROR)
927  {
928  goto error;
929  }
930  }
931 
932  /* Build the non leaf nodes of the btree; Root page id will be assigned here */
933 
934  if (btree_build_nleafs (thread_p, load_args, sort_args->n_nulls, sort_args->n_oids, load_args->n_keys) !=
935  NO_ERROR)
936  {
937  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_BTREE_LOAD_FAILED, 0);
938  goto error;
939  }
940 
941  /* There is at least one leaf page */
942 
943  /* Release the memory area */
944  os_free_and_init (load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.data);
945  os_free_and_init (load_args->ovf_recdes.data);
946  pr_clear_value (&load_args->current_key);
947 
948  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_LOG_BTREE_OPS))
949  {
950  _er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "DEBUG_BTREE: load built index btid (%d, (%d, %d)).",
951  load_args->btid->sys_btid->root_pageid, load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.volid,
952  load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.fileid);
953  }
954 
955 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
956  (void) btree_verify_tree (thread_p, &class_oids[0], &btid_int, bt_name);
957 #endif
958  }
959  else
960  {
961  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_LOG_BTREE_OPS))
962  {
963  _er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "DEBUG_BTREE: load didn't build any leaves btid (%d, (%d, %d)).",
964  load_args->btid->sys_btid->root_pageid, load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.volid,
965  load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.fileid);
966  }
967  /* redo an empty index, but first destroy the one we created. the safest way is to abort changes so far. */
968  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
969  is_sysop_started = false;
970 
971  os_free_and_init (load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.data);
972  os_free_and_init (load_args->ovf_recdes.data);
973  pr_clear_value (&load_args->current_key);
974 
975  BTID_SET_NULL (btid);
976  if (xbtree_add_index (thread_p, btid, key_type, &class_oids[0], attr_ids[0], unique_pk, sort_args->n_oids,
977  sort_args->n_nulls, load_args->n_keys) == NULL)
978  {
979  goto error;
980  }
981  }
982 
983  if (!VFID_ISNULL (&load_args->btid->ovfid))
984  {
985  /* notification */
986  if (!OID_ISNULL (&class_oids[0]))
987  {
988  notification_class_oid = &class_oids[0];
989  }
990  else
991  {
992  notification_class_oid = &btid_int.topclass_oid;
993  }
994  BTREE_SET_CREATED_OVERFLOW_KEY_NOTIFICATION (thread_p, NULL, NULL, notification_class_oid, btid, bt_name);
995  }
996 
997  if (sort_args->filter)
998  {
999  /* to clear db values from dbvalue regu variable */
1000  qexec_clear_pred_context (thread_p, sort_args->filter, true);
1001  }
1002  if (filter_pred != NULL && filter_pred->unpack_info != NULL)
1003  {
1004  stx_free_additional_buff (thread_p, filter_pred->unpack_info);
1005  stx_free_xasl_unpack_info (filter_pred->unpack_info);
1006  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, filter_pred->unpack_info);
1007  }
1008  if (sort_args->func_index_info && sort_args->func_index_info->expr)
1009  {
1010  (void) qexec_clear_func_pred (thread_p, (FUNC_PRED *) sort_args->func_index_info->expr);
1011  }
1012  if (func_unpack_info)
1013  {
1014  stx_free_additional_buff (thread_p, func_unpack_info);
1015  stx_free_xasl_unpack_info (func_unpack_info);
1016  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, func_unpack_info);
1017  }
1018 
1019  thread_p->pop_resource_tracks ();
1020 
1021  if (is_sysop_started)
1022  {
1023  /* todo: we have the option to commit & undo here. on undo, we can destroy the file directly. */
1024  log_sysop_attach_to_outer (thread_p);
1025  if (unique_pk)
1026  {
1027  /* drop statistics if aborted */
1028  log_append_undo_data2 (thread_p, RVBT_REMOVE_UNIQUE_STATS, NULL, NULL, NULL_OFFSET, sizeof (BTID), btid);
1029  }
1030  }
1031  else
1032  {
1033  /* index was not loaded and xbtree_add_index was called instead. we have nothing to log here. */
1034  }
1035 
1036  LOG_CS_ENTER (thread_p);
1037  logpb_flush_pages_direct (thread_p);
1038  LOG_CS_EXIT (thread_p);
1039 
1040  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_LOG_BTREE_OPS))
1041  {
1042  _er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "BTREE_DEBUG: load finished successful index btid(%d, (%d, %d)).",
1043  load_args->btid->sys_btid->root_pageid, load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.volid,
1044  load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.fileid);
1045  }
1046 
1047  return btid;
1048 
1049 error:
1050 
1051  if (!BTID_IS_NULL (&btid_global_stats))
1052  {
1053  logtb_delete_global_unique_stats (thread_p, &btid_global_stats);
1054  }
1055 
1056  if (sort_args->scancache_inited)
1057  {
1058  (void) heap_scancache_end (thread_p, &sort_args->hfscan_cache);
1059  }
1060  if (sort_args->attrinfo_inited)
1061  {
1062  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, &sort_args->attr_info);
1063  if (sort_args->filter)
1064  {
1065  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, sort_args->filter->cache_pred);
1066  }
1067  if (sort_args->func_index_info && sort_args->func_index_info->expr)
1068  {
1069  heap_attrinfo_end (thread_p, ((FUNC_PRED *) sort_args->func_index_info->expr)->cache_attrinfo);
1070  }
1071  }
1072  VFID_SET_NULL (&btid->vfid);
1073  btid->root_pageid = NULL_PAGEID;
1074  if (load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.data)
1075  {
1076  os_free_and_init (load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.data);
1077  }
1078  if (load_args->ovf_recdes.data)
1079  {
1080  os_free_and_init (load_args->ovf_recdes.data);
1081  }
1082  pr_clear_value (&load_args->current_key);
1083 
1084  if (load_args->leaf.pgptr)
1085  {
1086  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
1087  }
1088  if (load_args->ovf.pgptr)
1089  {
1090  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, load_args->ovf.pgptr);
1091  }
1092  if (load_args->nleaf.pgptr)
1093  {
1094  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1095  }
1096  if (load_args->push_list != NULL)
1097  {
1098  list_clear (load_args->push_list);
1099  load_args->push_list = NULL;
1100  }
1101  if (load_args->pop_list != NULL)
1102  {
1103  list_clear (load_args->pop_list);
1104  load_args->pop_list = NULL;
1105  }
1106 
1107  if (sort_args->filter)
1108  {
1109  /* to clear db values from dbvalue regu variable */
1110  qexec_clear_pred_context (thread_p, sort_args->filter, true);
1111  }
1112  if (filter_pred != NULL && filter_pred->unpack_info != NULL)
1113  {
1114  stx_free_additional_buff (thread_p, filter_pred->unpack_info);
1115  stx_free_xasl_unpack_info (filter_pred->unpack_info);
1116  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, filter_pred->unpack_info);
1117  }
1118  if (sort_args->func_index_info && sort_args->func_index_info->expr)
1119  {
1120  (void) qexec_clear_func_pred (thread_p, (FUNC_PRED *) sort_args->func_index_info->expr);
1121  }
1122  if (func_unpack_info)
1123  {
1124  stx_free_additional_buff (thread_p, func_unpack_info);
1125  stx_free_xasl_unpack_info (func_unpack_info);
1126  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, func_unpack_info);
1127  }
1128 
1129  thread_p->pop_resource_tracks ();
1130 
1131  if (is_sysop_started)
1132  {
1133  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
1134  }
1135 
1136  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_LOG_BTREE_OPS))
1137  {
1138  _er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE, "BTREE_DEBUG: load aborted index btid(%d, (%d, %d)).",
1139  load_args->btid->sys_btid->root_pageid, load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.volid,
1140  load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.fileid);
1141  }
1142 
1143  return NULL;
1144 }
1145 
1146 /*
1147  * btree_save_last_leafrec () - save the last leaf record
1148  * return: NO_ERROR
1149  * load_args(in): Collection of info. for btree load operation
1150  *
1151  * Note: Stores the last leaf record left in the load_args->out_recdes
1152  * area to the last leaf page (or to the last overflow page).
1153  * Then it saves the last leaf page (and the last overflow page,
1154  * if there is one) to the disk.
1155  */
1156 static int
1157 btree_save_last_leafrec (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOAD_ARGS * load_args)
1158 {
1159  INT16 slotid;
1160  int sp_success;
1161  int cur_maxspace;
1162  int ret = NO_ERROR;
1163  BTREE_NODE_HEADER *header = NULL;
1164 
1165  if (load_args->overflowing == true)
1166  {
1167  /* Store the record in current overflow page */
1168  sp_success = spage_insert (thread_p, load_args->ovf.pgptr, &load_args->ovf_recdes, &slotid);
1169  if (sp_success != SP_SUCCESS)
1170  {
1171  goto exit_on_error;
1172  }
1173 
1174  assert (slotid > 0);
1175 
1176  /* Save the current overflow page */
1177  btree_log_page (thread_p, &load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid, load_args->ovf.pgptr);
1178  load_args->ovf.pgptr = NULL;
1179  }
1180 
1181  /* Insert leaf record too */
1182  cur_maxspace = spage_max_space_for_new_record (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
1183  if (((cur_maxspace - load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.length) < LOAD_FIXED_EMPTY_FOR_LEAF)
1184  && (spage_number_of_records (load_args->leaf.pgptr) > 1))
1185  {
1186  /* New record does not fit into the current leaf page (within the threshold value); so allocate a new leaf page
1187  * and dump the current leaf page. */
1188  if (btree_proceed_leaf (thread_p, load_args) == NULL)
1189  {
1190  goto exit_on_error;
1191  }
1192  }
1193 
1194  /* Insert the record to the current leaf page */
1195  sp_success = spage_insert (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr, &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes, &slotid);
1196  if (sp_success != SP_SUCCESS)
1197  {
1198  goto exit_on_error;
1199  }
1200 
1201  assert (slotid > 0);
1202 
1203  /* Update the node header information for this record */
1204  if (load_args->cur_key_len >= BTREE_MAX_KEYLEN_INPAGE)
1205  {
1206  if (load_args->leaf.hdr.max_key_len < DISK_VPID_SIZE)
1207  {
1208  load_args->leaf.hdr.max_key_len = DISK_VPID_SIZE;
1209  }
1210  }
1211  else
1212  {
1213  if (load_args->leaf.hdr.max_key_len < load_args->cur_key_len)
1214  {
1215  load_args->leaf.hdr.max_key_len = load_args->cur_key_len;
1216  }
1217  }
1218 
1219  /* Update the leaf header of the current leaf page */
1220  header = btree_get_node_header (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
1221  if (header == NULL)
1222  {
1223  goto exit_on_error;
1224  }
1225 
1226  *header = load_args->leaf.hdr;
1227 
1228  /* Save the current leaf page */
1229  btree_log_page (thread_p, &load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
1230  load_args->leaf.pgptr = NULL;
1231 
1232  return ret;
1233 
1234 exit_on_error:
1235 
1236  if (load_args->leaf.pgptr)
1237  {
1238  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
1239  }
1240  if (load_args->ovf.pgptr)
1241  {
1242  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, load_args->ovf.pgptr);
1243  }
1244 
1245  return (ret == NO_ERROR && (ret = er_errid ()) == NO_ERROR) ? ER_FAILED : ret;
1246 }
1247 
1248 /*
1249  * btree_connect_page () - Connect child page to the new parent page
1250  * return: PAGE_PTR (pointer to the parent page if finished successfully,
1251  * or NULL in case of an error)
1252  * key(in): Biggest key value (or, separator value in case of string
1253  * keys) of the child page to be connected.
1254  * max_key_len(in): size of the biggest key in this leaf page
1255  * pageid(in): identifier of this leaf page
1256  * load_args(in):
1257  *
1258  * Note: This function connects a page to its parent page. In the
1259  * parent level a new record is prepared with the given & pageid
1260  * parameters and inserted into current non-leaf page being
1261  * filled up. If the record does not fit into this page within
1262  * the given threshold boundaries (LOAD_FIXED_EMPTY_FOR_NONLEAF bytes of each
1263  * page are reserved for future insertions) then this page is
1264  * flushed to disk and a new page is allocated to become the
1265  * current non-leaf page.
1266  */
1267 
1268 static PAGE_PTR
1269 btree_connect_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, DB_VALUE * key, int max_key_len, VPID * pageid, LOAD_ARGS * load_args,
1270  int node_level)
1271 {
1272  NON_LEAF_REC nleaf_rec;
1273  INT16 slotid;
1274  int sp_success;
1275  int cur_maxspace;
1276  int key_len;
1277  int key_type = BTREE_NORMAL_KEY;
1278  BTREE_NODE_HEADER *header = NULL;
1279 
1280  /* form the leaf record (create the header & insert the key) */
1281  cur_maxspace = spage_max_space_for_new_record (thread_p, load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1282 
1283  nleaf_rec.pnt = *pageid;
1284  key_len = btree_get_disk_size_of_key (key);
1285  if (key_len < BTREE_MAX_KEYLEN_INPAGE)
1286  {
1287  nleaf_rec.key_len = key_len;
1288  key_type = BTREE_NORMAL_KEY;
1289  }
1290  else
1291  {
1292  nleaf_rec.key_len = -1;
1293  key_type = BTREE_OVERFLOW_KEY;
1294 
1295  if (VFID_ISNULL (&load_args->btid->ovfid))
1296  {
1297  if (btree_create_overflow_key_file (thread_p, load_args->btid) != NO_ERROR)
1298  {
1299  return NULL;
1300  }
1301  }
1302  }
1303 
1304  if (btree_write_record (thread_p, load_args->btid, &nleaf_rec, key, BTREE_NON_LEAF_NODE, key_type, key_len, true,
1305  NULL, NULL, NULL, &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes) != NO_ERROR)
1306  {
1307  return NULL;
1308  }
1309 
1310  if ((cur_maxspace - load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.length) < LOAD_FIXED_EMPTY_FOR_NONLEAF)
1311  {
1312 
1313  /* New record does not fit into the current non-leaf page (within the threshold value); so allocate a new
1314  * non-leaf page and dump the current non-leaf page. */
1315 
1316  /* Update the non-leaf page header */
1317  header = btree_get_node_header (thread_p, load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1318  if (header == NULL)
1319  {
1320  return NULL;
1321  }
1322 
1323  *header = load_args->nleaf.hdr;
1324 
1325  /* Flush the current non-leaf page */
1326  btree_log_page (thread_p, &load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid, load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1327  load_args->nleaf.pgptr = NULL;
1328 
1329  /* Insert the pageid to the linked list */
1330  if (list_add (&load_args->push_list, &load_args->nleaf.vpid) != NO_ERROR)
1331  {
1332  return NULL;
1333  }
1334 
1335  /* get a new non-leaf page */
1336  if (btree_load_new_page (thread_p, load_args->btid->sys_btid, &load_args->nleaf.hdr, node_level,
1337  &load_args->nleaf.vpid, &load_args->nleaf.pgptr) != NO_ERROR)
1338  {
1339  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1340  return NULL;
1341  }
1342  if (load_args->nleaf.pgptr == NULL)
1343  {
1344  assert_release (false);
1345  return NULL;
1346  }
1347  } /* get a new leaf */
1348 
1349  /* Insert the record to the current leaf page */
1350  sp_success = spage_insert (thread_p, load_args->nleaf.pgptr, &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes, &slotid);
1351  if (sp_success != SP_SUCCESS)
1352  {
1353  return NULL;
1354  }
1355 
1356  assert (slotid > 0);
1357 
1358  /* Update the node header information for this record */
1359  if (load_args->nleaf.hdr.max_key_len < max_key_len)
1360  {
1361  load_args->nleaf.hdr.max_key_len = max_key_len;
1362  }
1363 
1364  return load_args->nleaf.pgptr;
1365 }
1366 
1367 /*
1368  * btree_build_nleafs () -
1369  * return: NO_ERROR
1370  * load_args(in): Collection of information on how to build B+tree.
1371  * n_nulls(in):
1372  * n_oids(in):
1373  * n_keys(in):
1374  *
1375  * Note: This function builds the non-leaf level nodes of the B+Tree
1376  * index in three phases. In the first phase, the first non-leaf
1377  * level nodes of the tree are constructed. Then, the upper
1378  * levels are built on top of this level, and finally, the last
1379  * non-leaf page (the single page of the top level) is updated
1380  * to become the root page.
1381  */
1382 static int
1383 btree_build_nleafs (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOAD_ARGS * load_args, int n_nulls, int n_oids, int n_keys)
1384 {
1385  RECDES temp_recdes; /* Temporary record descriptor; */
1386  char *temp_data = NULL;
1387  VPID next_vpid;
1388  PAGE_PTR next_pageptr = NULL;
1389 
1390  /* Variables used in the second phase to go over lower level non-leaf pages */
1391  VPID cur_nleafpgid;
1392  PAGE_PTR cur_nleafpgptr = NULL;
1393 
1394  BTREE_NODE *temp;
1395  BTREE_ROOT_HEADER root_header_info, *root_header = NULL;
1396  BTREE_NODE_HEADER *header = NULL;
1397  int key_cnt;
1398  int max_key_len, new_max;
1399  LEAF_REC leaf_pnt;
1400  NON_LEAF_REC nleaf_pnt;
1401  /* Variables for keeping keys */
1402  DB_VALUE prefix_key; /* Prefix key; prefix of last & first keys; used only if type is one of the string
1403  * types */
1404  int last_key_offset, first_key_offset;
1405  bool clear_last_key = false, clear_first_key = false;
1406 
1407  int ret = NO_ERROR;
1408  int node_level = 2; /* leaf level = 1, lowest non-leaf level = 2 */
1409  RECDES rec;
1410  char rec_buf[IO_MAX_PAGE_SIZE + BTREE_MAX_ALIGN];
1411  DB_VALUE last_key; /* Last key of the current page */
1412  DB_VALUE first_key; /* First key of the next page; used only if key_type is one of the string types */
1413 
1414  root_header = &root_header_info;
1415 
1416  rec.area_size = DB_PAGESIZE;
1417  rec.data = PTR_ALIGN (rec_buf, BTREE_MAX_ALIGN);
1418 
1419  db_make_null (&last_key);
1420  db_make_null (&first_key);
1421  db_make_null (&prefix_key);
1422 
1423  temp_data = (char *) os_malloc (DB_PAGESIZE);
1424  if (temp_data == NULL)
1425  {
1426  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, DB_PAGESIZE);
1427  ret = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
1428  goto end;
1429  }
1430 
1431  /*****************************************************
1432  PHASE I : Build the first non_leaf level nodes
1433  ****************************************************/
1434 
1435  assert (node_level == 2);
1436 
1437  /* Initialize the first non-leaf page */
1438  ret =
1439  btree_load_new_page (thread_p, load_args->btid->sys_btid, &load_args->nleaf.hdr, node_level, &load_args->nleaf.vpid,
1440  &load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1441  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1442  {
1443  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1444  goto end;
1445  }
1446  if (load_args->nleaf.pgptr == NULL)
1447  {
1448  assert_release (false);
1449  ret = ER_FAILED;
1450  goto end;
1451  }
1452 
1453  load_args->push_list = NULL;
1454  load_args->pop_list = NULL;
1455 
1456  db_make_null (&last_key);
1457 
1458  /* While there are some leaf pages do */
1459  load_args->leaf.vpid = load_args->vpid_first_leaf;
1460  while (!VPID_ISNULL (&(load_args->leaf.vpid)))
1461  {
1462  load_args->leaf.pgptr =
1463  pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &load_args->leaf.vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
1464  if (load_args->leaf.pgptr == NULL)
1465  {
1466  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (ret);
1467  goto end;
1468  }
1469 
1470  (void) pgbuf_check_page_ptype (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr, PAGE_BTREE);
1471 
1472  key_cnt = btree_node_number_of_keys (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
1473  assert (key_cnt > 0);
1474 
1475  /* obtain the header information for the leaf page */
1476  header = btree_get_node_header (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
1477  if (header == NULL)
1478  {
1479  assert_release (false);
1480  ret = ER_FAILED;
1481  goto end;
1482  }
1483 
1484  /* get the maximum key length on this leaf page */
1485  max_key_len = header->max_key_len;
1486  next_vpid = header->next_vpid;
1487 
1488  /* set level 2 to first non-leaf page */
1489  load_args->nleaf.hdr.node_level = node_level;
1490 
1491  /* Learn the first key of the leaf page */
1492  if (spage_get_record (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr, 1, &temp_recdes, PEEK) != S_SUCCESS)
1493 
1494  {
1495  assert_release (false);
1496  ret = ER_FAILED;
1497  goto end;
1498  }
1499 
1500  ret =
1501  btree_read_record (thread_p, load_args->btid, load_args->leaf.pgptr, &temp_recdes, &first_key, &leaf_pnt,
1502  BTREE_LEAF_NODE, &clear_first_key, &first_key_offset, PEEK_KEY_VALUE, NULL);
1503  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1504  {
1505  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1506  goto end;
1507  }
1508 
1509  if (pr_is_prefix_key_type (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (load_args->btid->key_type)))
1510  {
1511  /*
1512  * Key type is string or midxkey.
1513  * Should insert the prefix key to the parent level
1514  */
1515  if (DB_IS_NULL (&last_key))
1516  {
1517  /* is the first leaf When the types of leaf node are char, nchar, bit, the type that is saved on non-leaf
1518  * node is different. non-leaf spec (char -> varchar, nchar -> varnchar, bit -> varbit) hence it should
1519  * be configured by using setval of nonleaf_key_type. */
1520  ret = (*(load_args->btid->nonleaf_key_type->type->setval)) (&prefix_key, &first_key, true);
1521  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1522  {
1523  assert (!"setval error");
1524  goto end;
1525  }
1526  }
1527  else
1528  {
1529  /* Insert the prefix key to the parent level */
1530  ret = btree_get_prefix_separator (&last_key, &first_key, &prefix_key, load_args->btid->key_type);
1531  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1532  {
1533  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1534  goto end;
1535  }
1536  }
1537 
1538  /*
1539  * We may need to update the max_key length if the mid key is
1540  * larger than the max key length. This will only happen when
1541  * the varying key length is larger than the fixed key length
1542  * in pathological cases like char(4)
1543  */
1544  new_max = btree_get_disk_size_of_key (&prefix_key);
1545  new_max = BTREE_GET_KEY_LEN_IN_PAGE (new_max);
1546  max_key_len = MAX (new_max, max_key_len);
1547 
1548  assert (node_level == 2);
1549  if (btree_connect_page (thread_p, &prefix_key, max_key_len, &load_args->leaf.vpid, load_args, node_level) ==
1550  NULL)
1551  {
1552  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (ret);
1553  pr_clear_value (&prefix_key);
1554  goto end;
1555  }
1556 
1557  /* We always need to clear the prefix key. It is always a copy. */
1558  pr_clear_value (&prefix_key);
1559 
1560  btree_clear_key_value (&clear_last_key, &last_key);
1561 
1562  /* Learn the last key of the leaf page */
1563  assert (key_cnt > 0);
1564  if (spage_get_record (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr, key_cnt, &temp_recdes, PEEK) != S_SUCCESS)
1565  {
1566  assert_release (false);
1567  ret = ER_FAILED;
1568  goto end;
1569  }
1570 
1571  ret =
1572  btree_read_record (thread_p, load_args->btid, load_args->leaf.pgptr, &temp_recdes, &last_key, &leaf_pnt,
1573  BTREE_LEAF_NODE, &clear_last_key, &last_key_offset, PEEK_KEY_VALUE, NULL);
1574  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1575  {
1576  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1577  goto end;
1578  }
1579  }
1580  else
1581  {
1582  max_key_len = BTREE_GET_KEY_LEN_IN_PAGE (max_key_len);
1583 
1584  /* Insert this key to the parent level */
1585  assert (node_level == 2);
1586  if (btree_connect_page (thread_p, &first_key, max_key_len, &load_args->leaf.vpid, load_args, node_level) ==
1587  NULL)
1588  {
1589  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (ret);
1590  goto end;
1591  }
1592  }
1593 
1594  btree_clear_key_value (&clear_first_key, &first_key);
1595 
1596  /* Proceed the current leaf page pointer to the next leaf page */
1597  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
1598  load_args->leaf.vpid = next_vpid;
1599  load_args->leaf.pgptr = next_pageptr;
1600  next_pageptr = NULL;
1601 
1602  } /* while there are some more leaf pages */
1603 
1604 
1605  /* Update the non-leaf page header */
1606  header = btree_get_node_header (thread_p, load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1607  if (header == NULL)
1608  {
1609  assert_release (false);
1610  ret = ER_FAILED;
1611  goto end;
1612  }
1613 
1614  *header = load_args->nleaf.hdr;
1615 
1616  /* Flush the last non-leaf page */
1617  btree_log_page (thread_p, &load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid, load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1618  load_args->nleaf.pgptr = NULL;
1619 
1620  /* Insert the pageid to the linked list */
1621  ret = list_add (&load_args->push_list, &load_args->nleaf.vpid);
1622  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1623  {
1624  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1625  goto end;
1626  }
1627 
1628  btree_clear_key_value (&clear_last_key, &last_key);
1629 
1630  /*****************************************************
1631  PHASE II: Build the upper levels of tree
1632  ****************************************************/
1633 
1634  assert (node_level == 2);
1635 
1636  /* Switch the push and pop lists */
1637  load_args->pop_list = load_args->push_list;
1638  load_args->push_list = NULL;
1639 
1640  while (list_length (load_args->pop_list) > 1)
1641  {
1642  node_level++;
1643 
1644  /* while there are more than one page at the previous level do construct the next level */
1645 
1646  /* Initialize the first non-leaf page of current level */
1647  ret =
1648  btree_load_new_page (thread_p, load_args->btid->sys_btid, &load_args->nleaf.hdr, node_level,
1649  &load_args->nleaf.vpid, &load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1650  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1651  {
1652  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1653  goto end;
1654  }
1655  if (load_args->nleaf.pgptr == NULL)
1656  {
1657  assert_release (false);
1658  ret = ER_FAILED;
1659  goto end;
1660  }
1661 
1662  do
1663  { /* while pop_list is not empty */
1664  /* Get current pageid from the poplist */
1665  cur_nleafpgid = load_args->pop_list->pageid;
1666 
1667  /* Fetch the current page */
1668  cur_nleafpgptr = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &cur_nleafpgid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
1669  if (cur_nleafpgptr == NULL)
1670  {
1671  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (ret);
1672  goto end;
1673  }
1674 
1675  (void) pgbuf_check_page_ptype (thread_p, cur_nleafpgptr, PAGE_BTREE);
1676 
1677  /* obtain the header information for the current non-leaf page */
1678  header = btree_get_node_header (thread_p, cur_nleafpgptr);
1679  if (header == NULL)
1680  {
1681  assert_release (false);
1682  ret = ER_FAILED;
1683  goto end;
1684  }
1685 
1686  /* get the maximum key length on this leaf page */
1687  max_key_len = header->max_key_len;
1688 
1689  /* Learn the first key of the current page */
1690  /* Notice that since this is a non-leaf node */
1691  if (spage_get_record (thread_p, cur_nleafpgptr, 1, &temp_recdes, PEEK) != S_SUCCESS)
1692  {
1693  assert_release (false);
1694  ret = ER_FAILED;
1695  goto end;
1696  }
1697 
1698  ret =
1699  btree_read_record (thread_p, load_args->btid, cur_nleafpgptr, &temp_recdes, &first_key, &nleaf_pnt,
1700  BTREE_NON_LEAF_NODE, &clear_first_key, &first_key_offset, PEEK_KEY_VALUE, NULL);
1701  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1702  {
1703  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1704  goto end;
1705  }
1706 
1707  max_key_len = BTREE_GET_KEY_LEN_IN_PAGE (max_key_len);
1708 
1709  /* set level to non-leaf page nleaf page could be changed in btree_connect_page */
1710 
1711  assert (node_level > 2);
1712 
1713  load_args->nleaf.hdr.node_level = node_level;
1714 
1715  /* Insert this key to the parent level */
1716  if (btree_connect_page (thread_p, &first_key, max_key_len, &cur_nleafpgid, load_args, node_level) == NULL)
1717  {
1718  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (ret);
1719  goto end;
1720  }
1721 
1722  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, cur_nleafpgptr);
1723 
1724  /* Remove this pageid from the pop list */
1725  list_remove_first (&load_args->pop_list);
1726 
1727  btree_clear_key_value (&clear_first_key, &first_key);
1728  }
1729  while (list_length (load_args->pop_list) > 0);
1730 
1731  /* FLUSH LAST NON-LEAF PAGE */
1732 
1733  /* Update the non-leaf page header */
1734  header = btree_get_node_header (thread_p, load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1735  if (header == NULL)
1736  {
1737  assert_release (false);
1738  ret = ER_FAILED;
1739  goto end;
1740  }
1741 
1742  *header = load_args->nleaf.hdr;
1743 
1744  /* Flush the last non-leaf page */
1745  btree_log_page (thread_p, &load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid, load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1746  load_args->nleaf.pgptr = NULL;
1747 
1748  /* Insert the pageid to the linked list */
1749  ret = list_add (&load_args->push_list, &load_args->nleaf.vpid);
1750  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1751  {
1752  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1753  goto end;
1754  }
1755 
1756  /* Switch push and pop lists */
1757  temp = load_args->pop_list;
1758  load_args->pop_list = load_args->push_list;
1759  load_args->push_list = temp;
1760  }
1761 
1762  /* Deallocate the last node (only one exists) */
1763  list_remove_first (&load_args->pop_list);
1764 
1765  /******************************************
1766  PHASE III: Update the root page
1767  *****************************************/
1768 
1769  /* Retrieve the last non-leaf page (the current one); guaranteed to exist */
1770  /* Fetch the current page */
1771  load_args->nleaf.pgptr =
1772  pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &load_args->nleaf.vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
1773  if (load_args->nleaf.pgptr == NULL)
1774  {
1775  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (ret);
1776  goto end;
1777  }
1778  pgbuf_check_page_ptype (thread_p, load_args->nleaf.pgptr, PAGE_BTREE);
1779 
1780  /* Prepare the root header by using the last leaf node header */
1781  root_header->node.max_key_len = load_args->nleaf.hdr.max_key_len;
1782  root_header->node.node_level = node_level;
1783  VPID_SET_NULL (&(root_header->node.next_vpid));
1784  VPID_SET_NULL (&(root_header->node.prev_vpid));
1785  root_header->node.split_info.pivot = 0.0f;
1786  root_header->node.split_info.index = 0;
1787 
1788  if (load_args->btid->unique_pk)
1789  {
1790  root_header->num_nulls = n_nulls;
1791  root_header->num_oids = n_oids;
1792  root_header->num_keys = n_keys;
1793  root_header->unique_pk = load_args->btid->unique_pk;
1794 
1795  assert (BTREE_IS_UNIQUE (root_header->unique_pk));
1796  assert (BTREE_IS_PRIMARY_KEY (root_header->unique_pk) || !BTREE_IS_PRIMARY_KEY (root_header->unique_pk));
1797  }
1798  else
1799  {
1800  root_header->num_nulls = -1;
1801  root_header->num_oids = -1;
1802  root_header->num_keys = -1;
1803  root_header->unique_pk = 0;
1804  }
1805 
1806  COPY_OID (&(root_header->topclass_oid), &load_args->btid->topclass_oid);
1807 
1808  root_header->ovfid = load_args->btid->ovfid; /* structure copy */
1809  root_header->rev_level = BTREE_CURRENT_REV_LEVEL;
1810 
1811 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
1812  root_header->creator_mvccid = logtb_get_current_mvccid (thread_p);
1813 #else /* !SERVER_MODE */ /* SA_MODE */
1814  root_header->creator_mvccid = MVCCID_NULL;
1815 #endif /* SA_MODE */
1816 
1817  /* change node header as root header */
1818  ret = btree_pack_root_header (&rec, root_header, load_args->btid->key_type);
1819  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
1820  {
1821  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1822  goto end;
1823  }
1824 
1825  if (spage_update (thread_p, load_args->nleaf.pgptr, HEADER, &rec) != SP_SUCCESS)
1826  {
1827  assert_release (false);
1828  ret = ER_FAILED;
1829  goto end;
1830  }
1831 
1832  /* move current ROOT page content to the first page allocated */
1833  btree_get_root_vpid_from_btid (thread_p, load_args->btid->sys_btid, &cur_nleafpgid);
1834  next_pageptr = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &cur_nleafpgid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
1835  if (next_pageptr == NULL)
1836  {
1837  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (ret);
1838  goto end;
1839  }
1840  assert (pgbuf_get_page_ptype (thread_p, next_pageptr) == PAGE_BTREE);
1841 
1842  memcpy (next_pageptr, load_args->nleaf.pgptr, DB_PAGESIZE);
1843  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1844 
1845  load_args->nleaf.pgptr = next_pageptr;
1846  next_pageptr = NULL;
1847  load_args->nleaf.vpid = cur_nleafpgid;
1848 
1849  /* The root page must be logged, otherwise, in the event of a crash. The index may be gone. */
1850  btree_log_page (thread_p, &load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid, load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1851  load_args->nleaf.pgptr = NULL;
1852 
1853  assert (ret == NO_ERROR);
1854 
1855 end:
1856 
1857  /* cleanup */
1858  if (next_pageptr)
1859  {
1860  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, next_pageptr);
1861  }
1862  if (cur_nleafpgptr)
1863  {
1864  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, cur_nleafpgptr);
1865  }
1866  if (load_args->leaf.pgptr)
1867  {
1868  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
1869  }
1870  if (load_args->nleaf.pgptr)
1871  {
1872  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, load_args->nleaf.pgptr);
1873  }
1874  if (temp_data)
1875  {
1876  os_free_and_init (temp_data);
1877  }
1878 
1879  btree_clear_key_value (&clear_last_key, &last_key);
1880  btree_clear_key_value (&clear_first_key, &first_key);
1881 
1882  return ret;
1883 }

1885 /*
1886  * btree_log_page () - Save the contents of the buffer
1887  * return: nothing
1888  * vfid(in):
1889  * page_ptr(in): pointer to the page buffer to be saved
1890  *
1891  * Note: This function logs the contents of the given page and frees
1892  * the page after setting on the dirty bit.
1893  */
1894 static void
1895 btree_log_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, VFID * vfid, PAGE_PTR page_ptr)
1896 {
1897  LOG_DATA_ADDR addr; /* For recovery purposes */
1898 
1899  /* log the whole page for redo purposes. */
1900  addr.vfid = vfid;
1901  addr.pgptr = page_ptr;
1902  addr.offset = -1; /* irrelevant */
1903  log_append_redo_data (thread_p, RVBT_COPYPAGE, &addr, DB_PAGESIZE, page_ptr);
1904 
1905  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_ptr, FREE);
1906  page_ptr = NULL;
1907 }

1909 /*
1910  * btree_load_new_page () - load a new b-tree page.
1911  *
1912  * return : Error code
1913  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
1914  * btid (in) : B-tree identifier
1915  * header (in) : Node header for leaf/non-leaf nodes or NULL for overflow OID nodes
1916  * node_level (in) : Node level for leaf/non-leaf nodes or -1 for overflow OID nodes
1917  * vpid_new (out) : Output new page VPID
1918  * page_new (out) : Output new page
1919  */
1920 static int
1921 btree_load_new_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const BTID * btid, BTREE_NODE_HEADER * header, int node_level,
1922  VPID * vpid_new, PAGE_PTR * page_new)
1923 {
1924  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
1925 
1926  assert ((header != NULL && node_level >= 1) /* leaf, non-leaf */
1927  || (header == NULL && node_level == -1)); /* overflow */
1928  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p)); /* need system operation */
1929 
1930  /* we need to commit page allocations. if loading index is aborted, the entire file is destroyed. */
1931  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
1932 
1933  /* allocate new page */
1934  error_code = file_alloc (thread_p, &btid->vfid, btree_initialize_new_page, NULL, vpid_new, page_new);
1935  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1936  {
1937  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1938  goto end;
1939  }
1940  if (*page_new == NULL)
1941  {
1942  assert_release (false);
1943  error_code = ER_FAILED;
1944  goto end;
1945  }
1946  (void) pgbuf_check_page_ptype (thread_p, *page_new, PAGE_BTREE);
1947 
1948  if (header)
1949  { /* This is going to be a leaf or non-leaf page */
1950  /* Insert the node header (with initial values) to the leaf node */
1951  header->node_level = node_level;
1952  header->max_key_len = 0;
1953  VPID_SET_NULL (&header->next_vpid);
1954  VPID_SET_NULL (&header->prev_vpid);
1955  header->split_info.pivot = 0.0f;
1956  header->split_info.index = 0;
1957 
1958  error_code = btree_init_node_header (thread_p, &btid->vfid, *page_new, header, false);
1959  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1960  {
1961  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1962  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, *page_new);
1963  goto end;
1964  }
1965  }
1966  else
1967  { /* This is going to be an overflow page */
1968  BTREE_OVERFLOW_HEADER ovf_header_info;
1969 
1970  assert (node_level == -1);
1971  VPID_SET_NULL (&ovf_header_info.next_vpid);
1972 
1973  error_code = btree_init_overflow_header (thread_p, *page_new, &ovf_header_info);
1974  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1975  {
1976  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1977  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, *page_new);
1978  goto end;
1979  }
1980  }
1981 
1982  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
1983 
1984 end:
1985  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1986  {
1987  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
1988  }
1989  else
1990  {
1991  log_sysop_commit (thread_p);
1992  }
1993 
1994  return error_code;
1995 }

1997 /*
1998  * btree_proceed_leaf () - Proceed the current leaf page to a new one
1999  * return: PAGE_PTR (pointer to the new leaf page, or NULL in
2000  * case of an error).
2001  * load_args(in): Collection of information on how to build B+tree.
2002  *
2003  * Note: This function proceeds the current leaf page pointer from a
2004  * full leaf page to a new (completely empty) one. It first
2005  * allocates a new leaf page and connects it to the current
2006  * leaf page; then, it dumps the current one; and finally makes
2007  * the new leaf page "current".
2008  */
2009 static PAGE_PTR
2010 btree_proceed_leaf (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOAD_ARGS * load_args)
2011 {
2012  /* Local variables for managing leaf & overflow pages */
2013  VPID new_leafpgid;
2014  PAGE_PTR new_leafpgptr = NULL;
2015  BTREE_NODE_HEADER new_leafhdr, *header = NULL;
2016  RECDES temp_recdes; /* Temporary record descriptor; */
2017  OR_ALIGNED_BUF (sizeof (BTREE_NODE_HEADER)) a_temp_data;
2018 
2019  temp_recdes.data = OR_ALIGNED_BUF_START (a_temp_data);
2020  temp_recdes.area_size = sizeof (BTREE_NODE_HEADER);
2021 
2022  /* Allocate the new leaf page */
2023  if (btree_load_new_page (thread_p, load_args->btid->sys_btid, &new_leafhdr, 1, &new_leafpgid, &new_leafpgptr)
2024  != NO_ERROR)
2025  {
2026  ASSERT_ERROR ();
2027  return NULL;
2028  }
2029  if (new_leafpgptr == NULL)
2030  {
2031  assert_release (false);
2032  return NULL;
2033  }
2034 
2035  /* new leaf update header */
2036  new_leafhdr.prev_vpid = load_args->leaf.vpid;
2037 
2038  header = btree_get_node_header (thread_p, new_leafpgptr);
2039  if (header == NULL)
2040  {
2041  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, new_leafpgptr);
2042  return NULL;
2043  }
2044 
2045  *header = new_leafhdr; /* update header */
2046 
2047  /* current leaf update header */
2048  /* make the current leaf page point to the new one */
2049  load_args->leaf.hdr.next_vpid = new_leafpgid;
2050 
2051  /* and the new leaf point to the current one */
2052  header = btree_get_node_header (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
2053  if (header == NULL)
2054  {
2055  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, new_leafpgptr);
2056  return NULL;
2057  }
2058 
2059  *header = load_args->leaf.hdr;
2060 
2061  /* Flush the current leaf page */
2062  btree_log_page (thread_p, &load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
2063  load_args->leaf.pgptr = NULL;
2064 
2065  /* Make the new leaf page become the current one */
2066  load_args->leaf.vpid = new_leafpgid;
2067  load_args->leaf.pgptr = new_leafpgptr;
2068  load_args->leaf.hdr = new_leafhdr;
2069 
2070  return load_args->leaf.pgptr;
2071 }

2073 /*
2074  * btree_first_oid () - Prepare record for the key and its first oid
2075  * return: int
2076  * this_key(in): Key
2077  * class_oid(in):
2078  * first_oid(in): First OID associated with this key; inserted into the
2079  * record.
2080  * load_args(in): Contains fields specifying where & how to create the record
2081  *
2082  * Note: This function prepares the leaf record for the given key and

2084  * load_args->out_recdes field.

2087 btree_first_oid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, DB_VALUE * this_key, OID * class_oid, OID * first_oid,

2096 
2097  /* form the leaf record (create the header & insert the key) */
2098  key_len = load_args->cur_key_len = btree_get_disk_size_of_key (this_key);
2099  if (key_len < BTREE_MAX_KEYLEN_INPAGE)
2100  {
2101  key_type = BTREE_NORMAL_KEY;
2102  }
2103  else
2104  {

2113  }
2114  }

2117  btree_write_record (thread_p, load_args->btid, NULL, this_key, BTREE_LEAF_NODE, key_type, key_len, true, class_oid,
2118  first_oid, &mvcc_info, load_args->out_recdes);
2119  if (error != NO_ERROR)

2122  return error;

2124

2126  load_args->new_pos = (load_args->out_recdes->data + load_args->out_recdes->length);

2136 /*
2137  * btree_construct_leafs () - Output function for index sorting;constructs leaf
2138  * nodes
2139  * return: int
2140  * in_recdes(in): specifies the next sort item in the sorting order.
2141  * arg(in): output arguments; provides information about how to use the

2144  *
2145  * Note: This function creates the btree leaf nodes. It is passed

2149 static int

2151 {

2154  DB_VALUE this_key; /* Key value in this sorted item (specified with in_recdes) */

2187

2200  recdes = &sort_key_recdes;

2202  next_size = sizeof (char *);

2206

2225  goto error;
2226  }

2228

2231  if (ret != NO_ERROR)

2234  }

2240  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2241  {
2242  goto error;
2243  }
2244

2246  if (ret != NO_ERROR)

2250 
2251 #if defined(SERVER_MODE)

2255  MVCC_SET_FLAG_BITS (&mvcc_header, OR_MVCC_FLAG_VALID_INSID);
2256  }

2260 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */

2270 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */

2272

2279

2284  "mvccinfo=%llu| %llu", this_oid.volid, this_oid.pageid, this_oid.slotid, this_class_oid.volid,
2285  this_class_oid.pageid, this_class_oid.slotid, load_args->btid->sys_btid->root_pageid,
2286  load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.volid, load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.fileid,
2287  MVCC_GET_INSID (&mvcc_header), MVCC_GET_DELID (&mvcc_header));
2288  }
2289 
2290  /* Do not copy the string--just use the pointer. The pr_ routines for strings and sets have different semantics
2291  * for length. */
2292  if (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (load_args->btid->key_type) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY)
2293  {
2294  key_size = CAST_STRLEN (buf.endptr - buf.ptr);
2295  }
2296 
2297  ret = (*(load_args->btid->key_type->type->data_readval)) (&buf, &this_key, load_args->btid->key_type, key_size,
2298  copy, NULL, 0);
2299  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2300  {
2301  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_TF_CORRUPTED, 0);
2302  goto error;
2303  }
2304 
2305  /* Find out if this is the first call to this function */
2306  if (VPID_ISNULL (&(load_args->leaf.vpid)))
2307  {
2308  /* This is the first call to this function; so, initialize some fields in the LOAD_ARGS structure */
2309 
2310  /* Allocate the first page for the index */
2311  ret =

2313  &load_args->leaf.pgptr);
2314  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2315  {
2316  ASSERT_ERROR ();

2318  }
2319  if (load_args->leaf.pgptr == NULL || VPID_ISNULL (&load_args->leaf.vpid))
2320  {
2321  assert_release (false);
2322  goto error;
2323  }
2324  /* Save first leaf VPID. */
2325  load_args->vpid_first_leaf = load_args->leaf.vpid;
2326 
2327 #if 0 /* TODO: currently not used */
2328  load_args->first_leafpgid = load_args->leaf.vpid;
2329 #endif
2330  load_args->overflowing = false;
2331  assert (load_args->ovf.pgptr == NULL);
2332 
2333  /* Create the first record of the current page in main memory */
2334  load_args->out_recdes = &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes;
2335  ret = btree_first_oid (thread_p, &this_key, &this_class_oid, &this_oid, &mvcc_header, load_args);
2336  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2337  {
2338  goto error;
2339  }
2340 
2341  if (!MVCC_IS_HEADER_DELID_VALID (&mvcc_header))
2342  {
2343  /* Object was not deleted, increment curr_non_del_obj_count */
2344  load_args->curr_non_del_obj_count = 1;
2345 
2346  /* Increment the key counter if object is not deleted */
2347  (load_args->n_keys)++;
2348  }
2349  else
2350  {
2351  /* Object is deleted, initialize curr_non_del_obj_count as 0 */
2352  load_args->curr_non_del_obj_count = 0;
2353  }
2354 
2355  load_args->curr_rec_max_obj_count = BTREE_MAX_OIDCOUNT_IN_LEAF_RECORD (load_args->btid);
2356  load_args->curr_rec_obj_count = 1;
2357 
2358 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
2359  btree_check_valid_record (thread_p, load_args->btid, load_args->out_recdes, BTREE_LEAF_NODE, NULL);
2360 #endif
2361  }
2362  else
2363  { /* This is not the first call to this function */
2364  int c = DB_UNK;
2365 
2366  /*
2367  * Compare the received key with the current one.
2368  * If different, then dump the current record and create a new record.
2369  */
2370 
2371  c = btree_compare_key (&this_key, &load_args->current_key, load_args->btid->key_type, 0, 1, NULL);
2372  if (c == DB_EQ || c == DB_GT)
2373  {
2374  ; /* ok */
2375  }
2376  else
2377  {
2378  assert_release (false);
2379  goto error;
2380  }
2381 
2382  same_key = (c == DB_EQ) ? true : false;
2383 
2384  /* EQUALITY test only - doesn't care the reverse index */
2385 
2386  if (same_key)
2387  {
2388  /* This key (retrieved key) is the same with the current one. */
2389  load_args->curr_rec_obj_count++;
2390  if (!MVCC_IS_HEADER_DELID_VALID (&mvcc_header))
2391  {
2392  /* TODO: Rewrite btree_construct_leafs. It's almost impossible to follow. */
2393  load_args->curr_non_del_obj_count++;
2394  if (load_args->curr_non_del_obj_count > 1 && BTREE_IS_UNIQUE (load_args->btid->unique_pk))
2395  {
2396  /* Unique constrain violation - more than one visible records for this key. */
2397  BTREE_SET_UNIQUE_VIOLATION_ERROR (thread_p, &this_key, &this_oid, &this_class_oid,
2398  load_args->btid->sys_btid, load_args->bt_name);
2399  ret = ER_BTREE_UNIQUE_FAILED;
2400  goto error;
2401  }
2402  if (load_args->curr_non_del_obj_count == 1)
2403  {
2404  /* When first non-deleted object is found, we must increment that number of keys for statistics. */
2405  (load_args->n_keys)++;
2406 
2407  if (BTREE_IS_UNIQUE (load_args->btid->unique_pk))
2408  {
2409  /* this is the first non-deleted OID of the key; it must be placed as the first OID */
2410  BTREE_MVCC_INFO first_mvcc_info;
2411  OID first_oid, first_class_oid;
2412  int offset = 0;
2413 
2414  /* Retrieve the first OID from leaf record */
2415  ret =
2416  btree_leaf_get_first_object (load_args->btid, &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes, &first_oid,
2417  &first_class_oid, &first_mvcc_info);
2418  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2419  {
2420  goto error;
2421  }
2422 
2423  /* replace with current OID (might move memory in record) */
2424  btree_mvcc_info_from_heap_mvcc_header (&mvcc_header, &mvcc_info);
2425  btree_leaf_change_first_object (thread_p, &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes, load_args->btid,
2426  &this_oid, &this_class_oid, &mvcc_info, &offset, NULL, NULL);
2427  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2428  {
2429  goto error;
2430  }
2431 
2432  if (!load_args->overflowing)
2433  {
2434  /* Update load_args->new_pos in case record has grown after replace */
2435  load_args->new_pos += offset;
2436  }
2437 
2438  assert (load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.length <= load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.area_size);
2439 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
2440  btree_check_valid_record (thread_p, load_args->btid, &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes,
2441  BTREE_LEAF_NODE, NULL);
2442 #endif
2443 
2444  /* save first OID as current OID, to be written */
2445  COPY_OID (&this_oid, &first_oid);
2446  COPY_OID (&this_class_oid, &first_class_oid);
2447  btree_mvcc_info_to_heap_mvcc_header (&first_mvcc_info, &mvcc_header);
2448  }
2449  }
2450  }
2451 
2452  /* Check if there is space in the memory record for the new OID. If not dump the current record and
2453  * create a new record. */
2454 
2455  if (load_args->curr_rec_obj_count > load_args->curr_rec_max_obj_count)
2456  { /* There is no space for the new oid */
2457  if (load_args->overflowing == true)
2458  {
2459  /* Store the record in current overflow page */
2460  assert (load_args->out_recdes == &load_args->ovf_recdes);
2461  sp_success = spage_insert (thread_p, load_args->ovf.pgptr, &load_args->ovf_recdes, &slotid);
2462  if (sp_success != SP_SUCCESS)
2463  {
2464  goto error;
2465  }
2466 
2467  assert (slotid > 0);
2468 
2469  /* Allocate the new overflow page */
2470  ret =
2471  btree_load_new_page (thread_p, load_args->btid->sys_btid, NULL, -1, &new_ovfpgid,
2472  &new_ovfpgptr);
2473  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2474  {
2475  ASSERT_ERROR ();
2476  goto error;
2477  }
2478  if (new_ovfpgptr == NULL)
2479  {
2480  assert_release (false);
2481  ret = ER_FAILED;
2482  goto error;
2483  }
2484 
2485  /* make the current overflow page point to the new one */
2486  ovf_header = btree_get_overflow_header (thread_p, load_args->ovf.pgptr);
2487  if (ovf_header == NULL)
2488  {
2489  goto error;
2490  }
2491 
2492  ovf_header->next_vpid = new_ovfpgid;
2493 
2494  /* Save the current overflow page */
2495  btree_log_page (thread_p, &load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid, load_args->ovf.pgptr);
2496  load_args->ovf.pgptr = NULL;
2497 
2498  /* Make the new overflow page become the current one */
2499  load_args->ovf.vpid = new_ovfpgid;
2500  load_args->ovf.pgptr = new_ovfpgptr;
2501  new_ovfpgptr = NULL;
2502  }
2503  else
2504  { /* Current page is a leaf page */
2505  assert (load_args->out_recdes == &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes);
2506  /* Allocate the new overflow page */
2507  ret =
2508  btree_load_new_page (thread_p, load_args->btid->sys_btid, NULL, -1, &load_args->ovf.vpid,
2509  &load_args->ovf.pgptr);
2510  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2511  {
2512  ASSERT_ERROR ();
2513  goto error;
2514  }
2515  if (load_args->ovf.pgptr == NULL)
2516  {
2517  assert_release (false);
2518  goto error;
2519  }
2520 
2521  /* Connect the new overflow page to the leaf page */
2522  btree_leaf_record_change_overflow_link (thread_p, load_args->btid, &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes,
2523  &load_args->ovf.vpid, NULL, NULL);
2524 
2525  load_args->overflowing = true;
2526 
2527  /* Set out_recdes to ovf_recdes. */
2528  load_args->out_recdes = &load_args->ovf_recdes;
2529  } /* Current page is a leaf page */
2530 
2531  /* Initialize the memory area for the next record */
2532  assert (load_args->out_recdes == &load_args->ovf_recdes);
2533  load_args->out_recdes->length = 0;
2534  load_args->new_pos = load_args->out_recdes->data;
2535  load_args->curr_rec_max_obj_count =
2536  BTREE_MAX_OIDCOUNT_IN_SIZE (load_args->btid,
2537  spage_max_space_for_new_record (thread_p, load_args->ovf.pgptr));
2538  load_args->curr_rec_obj_count = 1;
2539  } /* no space for the new OID */
2540 
2541  if (load_args->overflowing || BTREE_IS_UNIQUE (load_args->btid->unique_pk))
2542  {
2543  /* all overflow OIDs have fixed header size; also, all OIDs of a unique index key (except the first
2544  * one) have fixed size */
2545  BTREE_MVCC_SET_HEADER_FIXED_SIZE (&mvcc_header);
2546  }
2547 
2548  /* Insert new OID, class OID (for unique), and MVCCID's. */
2549  /* Insert OID (and MVCC flags) */
2550  btree_set_mvcc_flags_into_oid (&mvcc_header, &this_oid);
2551  OR_PUT_OID (load_args->new_pos, &this_oid);
2552  load_args->out_recdes->length += OR_OID_SIZE;
2553  load_args->new_pos += OR_OID_SIZE;
2554 
2555  if (BTREE_IS_UNIQUE (load_args->btid->unique_pk))
2556  {
2557  /* Insert class OID */
2558  OR_PUT_OID (load_args->new_pos, &this_class_oid);
2559  load_args->out_recdes->length += OR_OID_SIZE;
2560  load_args->new_pos += OR_OID_SIZE;
2561  }
2562 
2563  btree_mvcc_info_from_heap_mvcc_header (&mvcc_header, &mvcc_info);
2564  /* Insert MVCCID's */
2565  load_args->out_recdes->length += btree_packed_mvccinfo_size (&mvcc_info);
2566  load_args->new_pos = btree_pack_mvccinfo (load_args->new_pos, &mvcc_info);
2567 
2568  assert (load_args->out_recdes->length <= load_args->out_recdes->area_size);
2569 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
2570  btree_check_valid_record (thread_p, load_args->btid, load_args->out_recdes,
2571  (load_args->overflowing ? BTREE_OVERFLOW_NODE : BTREE_LEAF_NODE), NULL);
2572 #endif
2573  } /* same key */
2574  else
2575  {
2576  /* Current key is finished; dump this output record to the disk page */
2577 
2578  /* Insert current leaf record */
2579  cur_maxspace = spage_max_space_for_new_record (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
2580  if (((cur_maxspace - load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes.length) < LOAD_FIXED_EMPTY_FOR_LEAF)
2581  && (spage_number_of_records (load_args->leaf.pgptr) > 1))
2582  {
2583  /* New record does not fit into the current leaf page (within the threshold value); so allocate a new
2584  * leaf page and dump the current leaf page. */
2585  if (btree_proceed_leaf (thread_p, load_args) == NULL)
2586  {
2587  goto error;
2588  }
2589  } /* get a new leaf */
2590 
2591  /* Insert the record to the current leaf page */
2592  sp_success =
2593  spage_insert (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr, &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes,
2594  &load_args->last_leaf_insert_slotid);
2595  if (sp_success != SP_SUCCESS)
2596  {
2597  goto error;
2598  }
2599 
2600  assert (load_args->last_leaf_insert_slotid > 0);
2601 
2602  /* Update the node header information for this record */
2603  if (load_args->cur_key_len >= BTREE_MAX_KEYLEN_INPAGE)
2604  {
2605  if (load_args->leaf.hdr.max_key_len < DISK_VPID_SIZE)
2606  {
2607  load_args->leaf.hdr.max_key_len = DISK_VPID_SIZE;
2608  }
2609  }
2610  else
2611  {
2612  if (load_args->leaf.hdr.max_key_len < load_args->cur_key_len)
2613  {
2614  load_args->leaf.hdr.max_key_len = load_args->cur_key_len;
2615  }
2616  }
2617 
2618  if (load_args->overflowing)
2619  {
2620  /* Insert the new record to the current overflow page and flush this page */
2621 
2622  assert (load_args->out_recdes == &load_args->ovf_recdes);
2623 
2624  /* Store the record in current overflow page */
2625  sp_success = spage_insert (thread_p, load_args->ovf.pgptr, load_args->out_recdes, &slotid);
2626  if (sp_success != SP_SUCCESS)
2627  {
2628  goto error;
2629  }
2630 
2631  assert (slotid > 0);
2632 
2633  /* Save the current overflow page */
2634  btree_log_page (thread_p, &load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid, load_args->ovf.pgptr);
2635  load_args->ovf.pgptr = NULL;
2636 
2637  /* Turn off the overflowing mode */
2638  load_args->overflowing = false;
2639  } /* Current page is an overflow page */
2640  else
2641  {
2642  assert (load_args->out_recdes == &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes);
2643  }
2644 
2645  /* Create the first part of the next record in main memory */
2646  load_args->out_recdes = &load_args->leaf_nleaf_recdes;
2647  ret = btree_first_oid (thread_p, &this_key, &this_class_oid, &this_oid, &mvcc_header, load_args);
2648  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2649  {
2650  goto error;
2651  }
2652 
2653  if (!MVCC_IS_HEADER_DELID_VALID (&mvcc_header))
2654  {
2655  /* Object was not deleted, increment curr_non_del_obj_count. */
2656  load_args->curr_non_del_obj_count = 1;
2657  (load_args->n_keys)++; /* Increment the key counter */
2658  }
2659  else
2660  {
2661  /* Object is deleted, initialize curr_non_del_obj_count as 0. */
2662  load_args->curr_non_del_obj_count = 0;
2663  }
2664 
2665  load_args->curr_rec_max_obj_count = BTREE_MAX_OIDCOUNT_IN_LEAF_RECORD (load_args->btid);
2666  load_args->curr_rec_obj_count = 1;
2667 
2668 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
2669  btree_check_valid_record (thread_p, load_args->btid, load_args->out_recdes, BTREE_LEAF_NODE, NULL);
2670 #endif
2671  } /* different key */
2672  }
2673 
2674  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_LOG_BTREE_OPS))
2675  {
2676  _er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE,
2677  "DEBUG_BTREE: load added object(%d, %d, %d) "
2678  "class(%d, %d, %d) and btid(%d, (%d, %d)) with mvccinfo=%llu | %llu", this_oid.volid,
2679  this_oid.pageid, this_oid.slotid, this_class_oid.volid, this_class_oid.pageid,
2680  this_class_oid.slotid, load_args->btid->sys_btid->root_pageid,
2681  load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.volid, load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.fileid,
2682  MVCC_GET_INSID (&mvcc_header), MVCC_GET_DELID (&mvcc_header));
2683  }
2684 
2685  /* Some objects have been recently deleted and couldn't be filtered (because there may be running transaction
2686  * that can still see them. However, they must be vacuumed later. Vacuum can only find them by parsing log,
2687  * therefore some log records are required. These are dummy records with the sole purpose of notifying vacuum.
2688  * Since this_oid, this_class_oid and mvcc_header could be replaced in case first object of unique index had to
2689  * be swapped, we will use original_oid, original_class_oid and original_mvcc_header to log object load for
2690  * vacuum. */
2691  if (MVCC_IS_HEADER_DELID_VALID (&original_mvcc_header)
2692  || MVCC_IS_HEADER_INSID_NOT_ALL_VISIBLE (&original_mvcc_header))
2693  {
2694  /* There is something to vacuum for this object */
2695  char *pgptr;
2696 
2697  pgptr = (load_args->overflowing ? load_args->ovf.pgptr : load_args->leaf.pgptr);
2698 
2699  /* clear flags for logging */
2700  btree_clear_mvcc_flags_from_oid (&original_oid);
2701 
2702  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_LOG_BTREE_OPS))
2703  {
2704  _er_log_debug (ARG_FILE_LINE,
2705  "DEBUG_BTREE: load notify vacuum object(%d, %d, %d) "
2706  "class(%d, %d, %d) and btid(%d, (%d, %d)) with mvccinfo=%llu | %llu",
2707  original_oid.volid, original_oid.pageid, original_oid.slotid, original_class_oid.volid,
2708  original_class_oid.pageid, original_class_oid.slotid,
2709  load_args->btid->sys_btid->root_pageid, load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.volid,
2710  load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid.fileid, MVCC_GET_INSID (&original_mvcc_header),
2711  MVCC_GET_DELID (&original_mvcc_header));
2712  }

2715  btree_mvcc_info_from_heap_mvcc_header (&original_mvcc_header, &mvcc_info);
2716  ret =

2718  BTREE_OP_NOTIFY_VACUUM, notify_vacuum_rv_data_bufalign,
2719  &notify_vacuum_rv_data, &notify_vacuum_rv_data_capacity,
2720  &notify_vacuum_rv_data_length);
2721  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
2722  {
2723  goto error;
2724  }
2725  log_append_undo_data2 (thread_p, RVBT_MVCC_NOTIFY_VACUUM, &load_args->btid->sys_btid->vfid, NULL, -1,
2726  notify_vacuum_rv_data_length, notify_vacuum_rv_data);
2727  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, pgptr, DONT_FREE);
2728  }
2729 
2730  /* set level 1 to leaf */
2731  load_args->leaf.hdr.node_level = 1;
2732 
2733  if (this_key.need_clear)
2734  {
2735  copy = true;
2736  }
2737 
2738  btree_clear_key_value (&copy, &this_key);
2739 
2740  if (next)
2741  { /* move to next link */
2742  recdes->data = next;
2743  recdes->length = SORT_RECORD_LENGTH (next);
2744  }
2745  else
2746  {
2747  break; /* exit infinite loop */
2748  }
2749 
2750  }
2751 
2752  if (notify_vacuum_rv_data != NULL && notify_vacuum_rv_data != notify_vacuum_rv_data_bufalign)
2753  {
2754  db_private_free (thread_p, notify_vacuum_rv_data);
2755  }
2756 
2757  assert (ret == NO_ERROR);
2758  return ret;
2759 
2760 error:
2761  if (load_args->leaf.pgptr)
2762  {
2763  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, load_args->leaf.pgptr);
2764  }
2765  if (load_args->ovf.pgptr)
2766  {
2767  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, load_args->ovf.pgptr);
2768  }
2769  if (new_ovfpgptr)
2770  {
2771  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, new_ovfpgptr);
2772  }
2773  btree_clear_key_value (&copy, &this_key);
2774 
2775  if (notify_vacuum_rv_data != NULL && notify_vacuum_rv_data != notify_vacuum_rv_data_bufalign)
2776  {
2777  db_private_free (thread_p, notify_vacuum_rv_data);
2778  }
2779 
2780  assert (er_errid () != NO_ERROR);
2781  return (ret == NO_ERROR && (ret = er_errid ()) == NO_ERROR) ? ER_FAILED : ret;
2782 }

3286 /*
3287  * compare_driver () -
3288  * return:
3289  * first(in):
3290  * second(in):
3291  * arg(in):
3292  */
3293 static int
3294 compare_driver (const void *first, const void *second, void *arg)
3295 {
3296  char *mem1 = *(char **) first;
3297  char *mem2 = *(char **) second;
3298  int has_null;
3299  SORT_ARGS *sort_args;
3300  TP_DOMAIN *key_type;
3301  int c = DB_UNK;
3302 
3303  sort_args = (SORT_ARGS *) arg;
3304  key_type = sort_args->key_type;
3305 
3306  assert (PTR_ALIGN (mem1, MAX_ALIGNMENT) == mem1);
3307  assert (PTR_ALIGN (mem2, MAX_ALIGNMENT) == mem2);
3308 
3309  /* Skip next link */
3310  mem1 += sizeof (char *);
3311  mem2 += sizeof (char *);
3312 
3313  /* Read value_has_null */
3314  assert (OR_GET_BYTE (mem1) == 0 || OR_GET_BYTE (mem1) == 1);
3315  assert (OR_GET_BYTE (mem2) == 0 || OR_GET_BYTE (mem2) == 1);
3316  has_null = (OR_GET_BYTE (mem1) || OR_GET_BYTE (mem2)) ? 1 : 0;
3317 
3318  mem1 += OR_INT_SIZE;
3319  mem2 += OR_INT_SIZE;
3320 
3321  assert (PTR_ALIGN (mem1, INT_ALIGNMENT) == mem1);
3322  assert (PTR_ALIGN (mem2, INT_ALIGNMENT) == mem2);
3323 
3324  /* Skip the oids */
3325  if (BTREE_IS_UNIQUE (sort_args->unique_pk))
3326  { /* unique index */
3327  mem1 += (2 * OR_OID_SIZE);
3328  mem2 += (2 * OR_OID_SIZE);
3329  }
3330  else
3331  { /* non-unique index */
3332  mem1 += OR_OID_SIZE;
3333  mem2 += OR_OID_SIZE;
3334  }
3335 
3336  assert (PTR_ALIGN (mem1, INT_ALIGNMENT) == mem1);
3337  assert (PTR_ALIGN (mem2, INT_ALIGNMENT) == mem2);
3338
