3340  mem1 += 2 * OR_MVCCID_SIZE;
3341  mem2 += 2 * OR_MVCCID_SIZE;
3342 
3343  assert (PTR_ALIGN (mem1, INT_ALIGNMENT) == mem1);
3344  assert (PTR_ALIGN (mem2, INT_ALIGNMENT) == mem2);
3345 
3346  if (TP_DOMAIN_TYPE (key_type) == DB_TYPE_MIDXKEY)
3347  {
3348  int i;
3349  char *bitptr1, *bitptr2;
3350  int bitmap_size;
3351  TP_DOMAIN *dom;
3352 
3353  /* fast implementation of pr_midxkey_compare (). do not use DB_VALUE container for speed-up */
3354 
3355  bitptr1 = mem1;
3356  bitptr2 = mem2;
3357 
3358  bitmap_size = OR_MULTI_BOUND_BIT_BYTES (key_type->precision);
3359 
3360  mem1 += bitmap_size;
3361  mem2 += bitmap_size;
3362 
3363 #if !defined(NDEBUG)
3364  for (i = 0, dom = key_type->setdomain; dom; dom = dom->next, i++);
3365  assert (i == key_type->precision);
3366 #endif
3367 
3368  if (sort_args->func_index_info != NULL)
3369  {
3370  assert (sort_args->n_attrs <= key_type->precision);
3371  }
3372  else
3373  {
3374  assert (sort_args->n_attrs == key_type->precision);
3375  }
3376  assert (key_type->setdomain != NULL);
3377 
3378  for (i = 0, dom = key_type->setdomain; i < key_type->precision && dom; i++, dom = dom->next)
3379  {
3380  /* val1 or val2 is NULL */
3381  if (has_null)
3382  {
3383  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_UNBOUND (bitptr1, i))
3384  { /* element val is null? */
3385  if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_UNBOUND (bitptr2, i))
3386  {
3387  continue;
3388  }
3389 
3390  c = DB_LT;
3391  break; /* exit for-loop */
3392  }
3393  else if (OR_MULTI_ATT_IS_UNBOUND (bitptr2, i))
3394  {
3395  c = DB_GT;
3396  break; /* exit for-loop */
3397  }
3398  }
3399 
3400  /* check for val1 and val2 same domain */

3402  assert (c == DB_LT || c == DB_EQ || c == DB_GT);
3403 
3404  if (c != DB_EQ)
3405  {
3406  break; /* exit for-loop */
3407  }
3408 
3409  mem1 += pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (mem1, dom);
3410  mem2 += pr_midxkey_element_disk_size (mem2, dom);

3412  assert (c == DB_LT || c == DB_EQ || c == DB_GT);

3414  if (dom && dom->is_desc)
3415  {
3416  c = ((c == DB_GT) ? DB_LT : (c == DB_LT) ? DB_GT : c);
3417  }
3418  }
3419  else
3420  {
3421  OR_BUF buf_val1, buf_val2;
3422  DB_VALUE val1, val2;
3423 
3424  OR_BUF_INIT (buf_val1, mem1, -1);
3425  OR_BUF_INIT (buf_val2, mem2, -1);
3426 
3427  if ((*(key_type->type->data_readval)) (&buf_val1, &val1, key_type, -1, false, NULL, 0) != NO_ERROR)
3428  {
3429  assert (false);
3430  return DB_UNK;
3431  }
3432 
3433  if ((*(key_type->type->data_readval)) (&buf_val2, &val2, key_type, -1, false, NULL, 0) != NO_ERROR)
3434  {
3435  assert (false);
3436  return DB_UNK;
3437  }
3438 
3439  c = btree_compare_key (&val1, &val2, key_type, 0, 1, NULL);
3440 
3441  /* Clear the values if it is required */
3442  if (DB_NEED_CLEAR (&val1))
3443  {
3444  pr_clear_value (&val1);
3445  }
3446 
3447  if (DB_NEED_CLEAR (&val2))
3448  {
3449  pr_clear_value (&val2);
3450  }
3451  }
3452 
3453  assert (c == DB_LT || c == DB_EQ || c == DB_GT);
3454 
3455  /* compare OID for non-unique index */
3456  if (c == DB_EQ)
3457  {
3458  OID first_oid, second_oid;
3459 
3460  mem1 = *(char **) first;
3461  mem2 = *(char **) second;
3462 
3463  /* Skip next link */
3464  mem1 += sizeof (char *);
3465  mem2 += sizeof (char *);
3466 
3467  /* Skip value_has_null */
3468  mem1 += OR_INT_SIZE;
3469  mem2 += OR_INT_SIZE;
3470 
3471  if (BTREE_IS_UNIQUE (sort_args->unique_pk))
3472  {
3473  /* Skip class OID */
3474  mem1 += OR_OID_SIZE;
3475  mem2 += OR_OID_SIZE;
3476  }
3477 
3478  OR_GET_OID (mem1, &first_oid);
3479  OR_GET_OID (mem2, &second_oid);
3480 
3481  assert_release (!OID_EQ (&first_oid, &second_oid));
3482 
3483  if (OID_LT (&first_oid, &second_oid))
3484  {
3485  c = DB_LT;
3486  }
3487  else
3488  {
3489  c = DB_GT;
3490  }
3491  }
3492 
3493  return c;
3494 }

3500 /*
3501  * list_add () -
3502  * return: NO_ERROR
3503  * list(in): which list to add
3504  * pageid(in): what value to put to the new node
3505  *
3506  * Note: This function adds a new node to the end of the given list.
3507  */
3508 static int
3509 list_add (BTREE_NODE ** list, VPID * pageid)
3510 {
3511  BTREE_NODE *new_node;
3512  BTREE_NODE *next_node;
3513  int ret = NO_ERROR;
3514 
3515  new_node = (BTREE_NODE *) os_malloc (sizeof (BTREE_NODE));
3516  if (new_node == NULL)
3517  {
3518  goto exit_on_error;
3519  }
3520 
3521  new_node->pageid = *pageid;
3522  new_node->next = NULL;
3523 
3524  if (*list == NULL)
3525  {
3526  *list = new_node;
3527  }
3528  else
3529  {
3530  next_node = *list;
3531  while (next_node->next != NULL)
3532  {
3533  next_node = next_node->next;
3534  }
3535 
3536  next_node->next = new_node;
3537  }
3538 
3539  return ret;
3540 
3541 exit_on_error:
3542 
3543  return (ret == NO_ERROR && (ret = er_errid ()) == NO_ERROR) ? ER_FAILED : ret;
3544 }

3704 /*
3705  * btree_load_check_fk () - Checks if the current foreign key that needs to be loaded is passing all the requirements.
3706  *
3707  * return: NO_ERROR or error code.
3708  * load_args(in): Context for the loaded index (Includes leaf level of the foreign key)
3709  * sort_args(in): Context for sorting (Includes info on primary key)
3710  *
3711  */
3712 int
3713 btree_load_check_fk (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const LOAD_ARGS * load_args, const SORT_ARGS * sort_args)
3714 {
3715  DB_VALUE fk_key, pk_key;
3716  int fk_node_key_cnt = -1, pk_node_key_cnt = -1;
3717  BTREE_NODE_HEADER *fk_node_header = NULL, *pk_node_header = NULL;
3718  VPID vpid;
3719  int ret = NO_ERROR, i;
3720  PAGE_PTR curr_fk_pageptr = NULL, old_page = NULL;
3721  INDX_SCAN_ID pk_isid;
3722  BTREE_SCAN pk_bt_scan;
3723  INT16 fk_slot_id = -1;
3724  bool found = false, pk_has_slot_visible = false, fk_has_visible = false;
3725  char *val_print = NULL;
3726  bool is_fk_scan_desc = false;
3727  MVCC_SNAPSHOT mvcc_snapshot_dirty;
3728  int lock_ret = LK_GRANTED;
3729  DB_VALUE_COMPARE_RESULT compare_ret;
3730  OR_CLASSREP *classrepr = NULL;
3731  int classrepr_cacheindex = -1, part_count = -1, pos = -1;
3732  bool clear_pcontext = false, has_partitions = false;
3733  PRUNING_CONTEXT pcontext;
3734  BTID pk_btid;
3735  OID pk_clsoid;
3736  HFID pk_dummy_hfid;
3737  BTREE_SCAN_PART partitions[MAX_PARTITIONS];
3738  bool has_nulls = false;
3739 
3740  db_make_null (&fk_key);
3741  db_make_null (&pk_key);
3742 
3743  mvcc_snapshot_dirty.snapshot_fnc = mvcc_satisfies_dirty;
3744 
3745  /* Initialize index scan on primary key btid. */
3746  scan_init_index_scan (&pk_isid, NULL, NULL);
3747  BTREE_INIT_SCAN (&pk_bt_scan);
3748 
3749  /* Lock the primary key class. */
3750  lock_ret = lock_object (thread_p, sort_args->fk_refcls_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, SIX_LOCK, LK_UNCOND_LOCK);
3751  if (lock_ret != LK_GRANTED)
3752  {
3753  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (ret);
3754  goto end;
3755  }
3756 
3757  /* Get class info for the primary key */
3758  classrepr = heap_classrepr_get (thread_p, sort_args->fk_refcls_oid, NULL, NULL_REPRID, &classrepr_cacheindex);
3759  if (classrepr == NULL)
3760  {
3761  ret = ER_FK_INVALID;
3762  goto end;
3763  }
3764 
3765  /* Primary key index search prepare */
3766  ret = btree_prepare_bts (thread_p, &pk_bt_scan, sort_args->fk_refcls_pk_btid, &pk_isid, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL,
3767  NULL, false, NULL);
3768  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3769  {
3770  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3771  goto end;
3772  }
3773 
3774  /* Set the order. */
3775  is_fk_scan_desc = (sort_args->key_type->is_desc != pk_bt_scan.btid_int.key_type->is_desc);
3776 
3777  /* Get the corresponding leaf of the foreign key. */
3778  if (!is_fk_scan_desc)
3779  {
3780  /* Get first leaf vpid. */
3781  vpid = load_args->vpid_first_leaf;
3782  }
3783  else
3784  {
3785  /* Get the last leaf. Current leaf is the last one. */
3786  vpid = load_args->leaf.vpid;
3787  }
3788 
3789  /* Init slot id */
3790  pk_bt_scan.slot_id = 0;
3791 
3792  /* Check if there are any partitions on the primary key. */
3793  if (classrepr->has_partition_info > 0)
3794  {
3795  (void) partition_init_pruning_context (&pcontext);
3796  clear_pcontext = true;
3797 
3798  ret = partition_load_pruning_context (thread_p, sort_args->fk_refcls_oid, DB_PARTITIONED_CLASS, &pcontext);
3799  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3800  {
3801  goto end;
3802  }
3803 
3804  /* Get number of partitions. */
3805  part_count = pcontext.count - 1; /* exclude partitioned table */
3806 
3807  assert (part_count <= MAX_PARTITIONS);
3808 
3809  /* Init context of each partition using the root context. */
3810  for (i = 0; i < part_count; i++)
3811  {
3812  memcpy (&partitions[i].pcontext, &pcontext, sizeof (PRUNING_CONTEXT));
3813  memcpy (&partitions[i].bt_scan, &pk_bt_scan, sizeof (BTREE_SCAN));
3814 
3815  partitions[i].bt_scan.btid_int.sys_btid = &partitions[i].btid;
3816  BTID_SET_NULL (&partitions[i].btid);
3817  partitions[i].header = NULL;
3818  partitions[i].key_cnt = -1;
3819  }
3820 
3821  has_partitions = true;
3822  }
3823 
3824  while (true)
3825  {
3826  ret = btree_advance_to_next_slot_and_fix_page (thread_p, sort_args->btid, &vpid, &curr_fk_pageptr, &fk_slot_id,
3827  &fk_key, is_fk_scan_desc, &fk_node_key_cnt, &fk_node_header,
3828  &mvcc_snapshot_dirty);
3829  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3830  {
3831  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3832  break;
3833  }
3834 
3835  has_nulls = false;
3836 
3837  if (curr_fk_pageptr == NULL)
3838  {
3839  /* Search has ended. */
3840  break;
3841  }
3842 
3843  if (DB_IS_NULL (&fk_key))
3844  {
3845  /* Only way to get this is by having no visible objects in the foreign key. */
3846  /* Must be checked!! */
3847  break;
3848  }
3849 
3850  /* Check for multi col nulls. */
3851  if (sort_args->n_attrs > 1)
3852  {
3853  has_nulls = btree_multicol_key_has_null (&fk_key);
3854  }
3855  else
3856  {
3857  /* TODO: unreachable case */
3858  has_nulls = DB_IS_NULL (&fk_key);
3859  }
3860 
3861  if (has_nulls)
3862  {
3863  /* ANSI SQL says
3864  *
3865  * The choices for <match type> are MATCH SIMPLE, MATCH PARTIAL, and MATCH FULL; MATCH SIMPLE is the default.
3866  * There is no semantic difference between these choices if there is only one referencing column (and, hence,
3867  * only one referenced column). There is also no semantic difference if all referencing columns are not
3868  * nullable. If there is more than one referencing column, at least one of which is nullable, and
3869  * if no <referencing period specification> is specified, then the various <match type>s have the following
3870  * semantics:
3871  *
3872  * MATCH SIMPLE: if at least one referencing column is null, then the row of the referencing table passes
3873  * the constraint check. If all referencing columns are not null, then the row passes the constraint check
3874  * if and only if there is a row of the referenced table that matches all the referencing columns.
3875  * MATCH PARTIAL: if all referencing columns are null, then the row of the referencing table passes
3876  * the constraint check. If at least one referencing columns is not null, then the row passes the constraint
3877  * check if and only if there is a row of the referenced table that matches all the non-null referencing
3878  * columns.
3879  * MATCH FULL: if all referencing columns are null, then the row of the referencing table passes
3880  * the constraint check. If all referencing columns are not null, then the row passes the constraint check
3881  * if and only if there is a row of the referenced table that matches all the referencing columns. If some
3882  * referencing column is null and another referencing column is non-null, then the row of the referencing
3883  * table violates the constraint check.
3884  *
3885  * In short, we don't provide options for <match type> and our behavior is <MATCH SIMPLE> which is
3886  * the default behavior of ANSI SQL and the other (commercial) products.
3887  */
3888 
3889  /* Skip current key. */
3890  continue;
3891  }
3892 
3893  /* We got the value from the foreign key, now search through the primary key index. */
3894  found = false;
3895 
3896  if (has_partitions)
3897  {
3898  COPY_OID (&pk_clsoid, sort_args->fk_refcls_oid);
3899  BTID_COPY (&pk_btid, sort_args->fk_refcls_pk_btid);
3900 
3901  /* Get the correct oid, btid and partition of the key we are looking for. */
3902  ret = partition_prune_partition_index (&pcontext, &fk_key, &pk_clsoid, &pk_btid, &pos);
3903  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3904  {
3905  break;
3906  }
3907 
3908  if (BTID_IS_NULL (&partitions[pos].btid))
3909  {
3910  /* No need to lock individual partitions here, since the partitioned table is already locked */
3911  ret = partition_prune_unique_btid (&pcontext, &fk_key, &pk_clsoid, &pk_dummy_hfid, &pk_btid);
3912  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3913  {
3914  break;
3915  }
3916 
3917  /* Update the partition BTID. */
3918  BTID_COPY (&partitions[pos].btid, &pk_btid);
3919  }
3920 
3921  /* Save the old page, if any. */
3922  if (pk_bt_scan.C_page != NULL)
3923  {
3924  old_page = pk_bt_scan.C_page;
3925  }
3926 
3927  /* Update references. */
3928  pk_bt_scan = partitions[pos].bt_scan;
3929  pk_node_key_cnt = partitions[pos].key_cnt;
3930  pk_node_header = partitions[pos].header;
3931  }
3932 
3933  /* Search through the primary key index. */
3934  if (pk_bt_scan.C_page == NULL)
3935  {
3936  /* No search has been initiated yet, we start from root. */
3937  ret = btree_locate_key (thread_p, &pk_bt_scan.btid_int, &fk_key, &pk_bt_scan.C_vpid, &pk_bt_scan.slot_id,
3938  &pk_bt_scan.C_page, &found);
3939  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3940  {
3941  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3942  break;
3943  }
3944  else if (!found)
3945  {
3946  /* Value was not found at all, it means the foreign key is invalid. */
3947  val_print = pr_valstring (thread_p, &fk_key);
3948  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_FK_INVALID, 2, sort_args->fk_name,
3949  (val_print ? val_print : "unknown value"));
3950  ret = ER_FK_INVALID;
3951  db_private_free (thread_p, val_print);
3952  break;
3953  }
3954  else
3955  {
3956  /* First unfix the old page if applicable. The new page was fixed in btree_locate_key. */
3957  if (old_page != NULL)
3958  {
3959  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, old_page);
3960  }
3961 
3962  /* Make sure there is at least one visible object. */
3963  ret = btree_is_slot_visible (thread_p, &pk_bt_scan.btid_int, pk_bt_scan.C_page, &mvcc_snapshot_dirty,
3964  pk_bt_scan.slot_id, &pk_has_slot_visible);
3965  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3966  {
3967  break;
3968  }
3969 
3970  if (!pk_has_slot_visible)
3971  {
3972  /* No visible object in current page, but the key was located here. Should not happen often. */
3973  val_print = pr_valstring (thread_p, &fk_key);
3974  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_FK_INVALID, 2, sort_args->fk_name,
3975  (val_print ? val_print : "unknown value"));
3976  ret = ER_FK_INVALID;
3977  db_private_free (thread_p, val_print);
3978  break;
3979  }
3980 
3981  assert (pk_bt_scan.C_page != NULL);
3982  }
3983 
3984  /* Unfix old page, if any. */
3985  if (old_page != NULL)
3986  {
3987  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, old_page);
3988  }
3989  }
3990  else
3991  {
3992  /* We try to resume the search in the current leaf. */
3993  while (!found)
3994  {
3995  ret = btree_advance_to_next_slot_and_fix_page (thread_p, &pk_bt_scan.btid_int, &pk_bt_scan.C_vpid,
3996  &pk_bt_scan.C_page, &pk_bt_scan.slot_id, &pk_key, false,
3997  &pk_node_key_cnt, &pk_node_header, &mvcc_snapshot_dirty);
3998  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
3999  {
4000  goto end;
4001  }
4002 
4003  if (pk_bt_scan.C_page == NULL)
4004  {
4005  /* The primary key has ended, but the value from foreign key was not found. */
4006  /* Foreign key is invalid. Set error. */
4007  val_print = pr_valstring (thread_p, &fk_key);
4008  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_FK_INVALID, 2, sort_args->fk_name,
4009  (val_print ? val_print : "unknown value"));
4010  ret = ER_FK_INVALID;
4011  db_private_free (thread_p, val_print);
4012  goto end;
4013  }
4014 
4015  /* We need to compare the current value with the new value from the primary key. */
4016  compare_ret = btree_compare_key (&pk_key, &fk_key, pk_bt_scan.btid_int.key_type, 1, 1, NULL);
4017  if (compare_ret == DB_EQ)
4018  {
4019  /* Found value, stop searching in pk. */
4020  break;
4021  }
4022  else if (compare_ret == DB_LT)
4023  {
4024  /* No match yet. Advance in pk. */
4025  continue;
4026  }
4027  else
4028  {
4029  /* Fk is invalid. Set error. */
4030  val_print = pr_valstring (thread_p, &fk_key);
4031  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_FK_INVALID, 2, sort_args->fk_name,
4032  (val_print ? val_print : "unknown value"));
4033  ret = ER_FK_INVALID;
4034  db_private_free (thread_p, val_print);
4035  goto end;
4036  }
4037  }
4038 
4039  if (!found && pk_bt_scan.slot_id > pk_node_key_cnt)
4040  {
4041  old_page = pk_bt_scan.C_page;
4042  pk_bt_scan.C_page = NULL;
4043  }

4150 /*
4151  * btree_advance_to_next_slot_and_fix_page () -
4152  *
4153  * return: NO_ERROR or error code
4154  * btid(in): B-tree structure
4155  * vpid(in/out): VPID of the current page
4156  * pg_ptr(in/out): Page pointer for the current page.
4157  * slot_id(in/out): Slot id of the current/next value.
4158  * key(out): Requested key.
4159  * key_cnt(in/out): Number of keys in current page.
4160  * header(in/out): The header of the current page.
4161  * mvcc(in): Needed for visibility check.
4162  *
4163  * Note:
4164  * This function will advance to a next page without using conditional latches.
4165  * Therefore, if this is used for a descending scan, it might not work properly
4166  * unless concurrency is guaranteed.
4167  */
4168 static int
4169 btree_advance_to_next_slot_and_fix_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, BTID_INT * btid, VPID * vpid, PAGE_PTR * pg_ptr,
4170  INT16 * slot_id, DB_VALUE * key, bool is_desc, int *key_cnt,
4171  BTREE_NODE_HEADER ** header, MVCC_SNAPSHOT * mvcc)
4172 {
4173  int ret = NO_ERROR;
4174  VPID next_vpid;
4175  PAGE_PTR page = *pg_ptr;
4176  BTREE_NODE_HEADER *local_header = *header;
4177  bool is_slot_visible = false;
4178  PAGE_PTR old_page = NULL;
4179 
4180  /* Clear current key, if any. */
4181  if (!DB_IS_NULL (key))
4182  {
4183  pr_clear_value (key);
4184  }
4185 
4186  if (page == NULL)
4187  {
4188  page = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
4189  if (page == NULL)
4190  {
4191  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (ret);
4192  return ret;
4193  }
4194 
4195  *slot_id = -1;
4196  }
4197 
4198  assert (page != NULL);
4199 
4200  /* Check page. */
4201  (void) pgbuf_check_page_ptype (thread_p, page, PAGE_BTREE);
4202 
4203  if (local_header == NULL)
4204  {
4205  /* Get the header of the page. */
4206  local_header = btree_get_node_header (thread_p, page);
4207  }
4208 
4209  if (*key_cnt == -1)
4210  {
4211  /* Get number of keys in page. */
4212  *key_cnt = btree_node_number_of_keys (thread_p, page);
4213  }
4214 
4215  /* If it is the first search. */
4216  if (*slot_id == -1)
4217  {
4218  *slot_id = is_desc ? (*key_cnt + 1) : 0;
4219  }
4220 
4221  /* Advance to next key. */
4222  while (true)
4223  {
4224  *slot_id += (is_desc ? -1 : 1);
4225  assert (0 <= *slot_id);
4226 
4227  if (*slot_id == 0 || *slot_id >= *key_cnt + 1)
4228  {
4229  next_vpid = is_desc ? local_header->prev_vpid : local_header->next_vpid;
4230  if (VPID_ISNULL (&next_vpid))
4231  {
4232  /* No next page. unfix current one. */
4233  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page);
4234  break;
4235  }
4236  else
4237  {
4238  old_page = page;
4239  page = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &next_vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
4240  if (page == NULL)
4241  {
4242  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (ret);
4243  return ret;
4244  }
4245 
4246  /* unfix old page */
4247  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, old_page);
4248 
4249  *slot_id = is_desc ? *key_cnt : 1;
4250 
4251  /* Get the new header. */
4252  local_header = btree_get_node_header (thread_p, page);
4253 
4254  /* Get number of keys in new page. */
4255  *key_cnt = btree_node_number_of_keys (thread_p, page);
4256  }
4257  }
4258 
4259  if (mvcc != NULL)
4260  {
4261  ret = btree_is_slot_visible (thread_p, btid, page, mvcc, *slot_id, &is_slot_visible);
4262  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
4263  {
4264  return ret;
4265  }
4266 
4267  if (!is_slot_visible)
4268  {
4269  continue;
4270  }
4271  }
4272 
4273  /* The slot is visible. Fall through and get the key. */
4274  break;
4275  }
4276 
4277  if (page != NULL)
4278  {
4279  ret = btree_get_value_from_leaf_slot (thread_p, btid, page, *slot_id, key);
4280  }
4281 
4282  *header = local_header;
4283  *pg_ptr = page;
4284 
4285  return ret;
4286 }

4288 /*
4289  * btree_is_slot_visible(): States if current slot is visible or not.
4290  *
4291  * thread_p(in): Thread entry.
4292  * btid(in): B-tree info.
4293  * pg_ptr(in): Page pointer.
4294  * mvcc_snapshot(in): The MVCC snapshot.
4295  * slot_id(in) : Slot id to be looked for.
4296  * is_visible(out): True or False
4297  *
4298  * return: error code if any error occurs.
4299  */
4300 static int
4301 btree_is_slot_visible (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, BTID_INT * btid, PAGE_PTR pg_ptr, MVCC_SNAPSHOT * mvcc_snapshot,
4302  int slot_id, bool * is_visible)
4303 {
4304  RECDES record;
4305  LEAF_REC leaf;
4306  int num_visible = 0;
4307  int key_offset = 0;
4308  int ret = NO_ERROR;
4309  bool dummy_clear_key;
4310 
4311  *is_visible = false;
4312 
4313  if (mvcc_snapshot == NULL)
4314  {
4315  /* Early out. */
4316  *is_visible = true;
4317  return ret;
4318  }
4319 
4320  /* Get the record. */
4321  if (spage_get_record (thread_p, pg_ptr, slot_id, &record, PEEK) != S_SUCCESS)
4322  {
4323  assert_release (false);
4324  ret = ER_FAILED;
4325  return ret;
4326  }
4327 
4328  /* Read the record. - no need of actual key value */
4329  ret = btree_read_record (thread_p, btid, pg_ptr, &record, NULL, &leaf, BTREE_LEAF_NODE, &dummy_clear_key,
4330  &key_offset, PEEK_KEY_VALUE, NULL);
4331  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
4332  {
4333  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4334  return ret;
4335  }
4336 
4337  /* Get the number of visible items. */
4338  ret = btree_get_num_visible_from_leaf_and_ovf (thread_p, btid, &record, key_offset, &leaf, NULL, mvcc_snapshot,
4339  &num_visible);
4340  if (ret != NO_ERROR)
4341  {
4342  return ret;
4343  }
4344 
4345  if (num_visible > 0)
4346  {
4347  *is_visible = true;
4348  }
4349 
4350  return ret;
4351 }
